# === finding-20ca8dc3-3ace-459f-b5d0-fbacca545ffc ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-20ca8dc3-3ace-459f-b5d0-fbacca545ffc> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:02:06.383476Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Apple Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:02:06.383338+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "I now have comprehensive data. Here's a full summary of findings:\n\n---\n\n## Apple Fiscal Q1 2026 (Calendar Q4 2025) Earnings — Research Summary\n\n**Reported:** January 29, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n- **Revenue: $143.8 billion** — up **16% YoY** (all-time record)\n- Beat analyst consensus estimate of **$138.48 billion**\n- Net profit: **$42.1 billion**\n- Gross margin: **48.2%** (vs. 46.9% prior year)\n- Operating cash flow: **$53.9 billion**\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Analyst Estimates\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Beat? |\n|--------|--------|----------|-------|\n| EPS (diluted) | **$2.84** | $2.67 | +$0.17 ✓ |\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | $138.48B | +$5.3B ✓ |\n\nEPS up **19% YoY** — new all-time EPS record.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Revenue by Segment\n| Segment | Q1 FY2026 | YoY Change |\n|---------|-----------|------------|\n| **iPhone** | $85.3B | +23.3% (all-time record) |\n| **Services** | ~$30.0B | +13.9% (all-time record) |\n| **iPad** | $8.6B | +6.3% |\n| **Mac** | $8.4B | -6.7% |\n| **Wearables/Home/Accessories** | $11.5B | -2.2% |\n\n**iPhone** was the standout, driven by strong iPhone 17 demand. **Services** hit a new all-time high. **Mac** and **Wearables** were the two weak spots, declining YoY.\n\n**Geographic highlights:**\n- Greater China: **+37.9% YoY** (~$25.5B) — standout region\n- Rest of Asia Pacific: +18.0%\n- Europe: +12.7%\n- Americas: +11.2%\n- Japan: +4.7%\n\n---\n\n### 4. Forward Guidance (Q2 FY2026 / January–March 2026)\n- Revenue growth: **+13–16% YoY**\n- Gross margin: **48–49%**\n- Operating expenses: **$18.4–$18.7 billion**\n- Tariff impact anticipated: ~**$1.4 billion** (same as Q1 FY2026 impact)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Management Commentary\n- **Tim Cook (CEO):** iPhone demand was \"simply staggering\" with \"all-time records across every geographic segment.\" Highlighted 2.5 billion active devices in the installed base and expanding AI investment.\n- **Kevan Parekh (CFO):** Cited record EPS growth of 19%, operating cash flow of $53.9 billion, and ~$32 billion returned to shareholders. Noted $1.4B tariff headwind in the quarter. Emphasized R&D-driven opex increases tied to AI.\n\n---\n\n### Data Notes\n- Services revenue: one source cited $26.34B (likely the year-ago comparable), while MacRumors detailed breakdown shows **~$30B** for Q1 FY2026, which is more consistent with Q4 FY2025's $28.8B Services figure.\n- The quarter delivered all-time records for: total revenue, EPS, iPhone revenue, and Services revenue.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Apple Reports Record-Setting 1Q 2026 Results — MacRumors](https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/29/apple-1q-2026-earnings/)\n- [Apple reports first quarter results — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple beats Wall Street expectations — The Desk](https://thedesk.net/2026/01/apple-fiscal-q1-2026-earnings-report/)\n- [Apple Q4 2025: Record $102.5B Revenue — The Acquirer's Multiple](https://acquirersmultiple.com/2025/11/apple-q4-2025-record-102-5b-revenue-surging-services-and-ai-powered-future/)\n- [Apple AAPL Q1 2026 Earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "b9865c74-8778-4bd3-a0db-91b32b79b7a6" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "I now have comprehensive data. Here's a full summary of findings:\n\n---\n\n## Apple Fiscal Q1 2026 (Calendar Q4 2025) Earnings — Research Summary\n\n**Reported:** January 29, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n- **Revenue: $143.8 billion** — up **16% YoY** (all-time record)\n- Beat analyst consensus estimate of **$138.48 billion**\n- Net profit: **$42.1 billion**\n- Gross margin: **48.2%** (vs. 46.9% prior year)\n- Operating cash flow: **$53.9 billion**\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Analyst Estimates\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Beat? |\n|--------|--------|----------|-------|\n| EPS (diluted) | **$2.84** | $2.67 | +$0.17 ✓ |\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | $138.48B | +$5.3B ✓ |\n\nEPS up **19% YoY** — new all-time EPS record.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Revenue by Segment\n| Segment | Q1 FY2026 | YoY Change |\n|---------|-----------|------------|\n| **iPhone** | $85.3B | +23.3% (all-time record) |\n| **Services** | ~$30.0B | +13.9% (all-time record) |\n| **iPad** | $8.6B | +6.3% |\n| **Mac** | $8.4B | -6.7% |\n| **Wearables/Home/Accessories** | $11.5B | -2.2% |\n\n**iPhone** was the standout, driven by strong iPhone 17 demand. **Services** hit a new all-time high. **Mac** and **Wearables** were the two weak spots, declining YoY.\n\n**Geographic highlights:**\n- Greater China: **+37.9% YoY** (~$25.5B) — standout region\n- Rest of Asia Pacific: +18.0%\n- Europe: +12.7%\n- Americas: +11.2%\n- Japan: +4.7%\n\n---\n\n### 4. Forward Guidance (Q2 FY2026 / January–March 2026)\n- Revenue growth: **+13–16% YoY**\n- Gross margin: **48–49%**\n- Operating expenses: **$18.4–$18.7 billion**\n- Tariff impact anticipated: ~**$1.4 billion** (same as Q1 FY2026 impact)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Management Commentary\n- **Tim Cook (CEO):** iPhone demand was \"simply staggering\" with \"all-time records across every geographic segment.\" Highlighted 2.5 billion active devices in the installed base and expanding AI investment.\n- **Kevan Parekh (CFO):** Cited record EPS growth of 19%, operating cash flow of $53.9 billion, and ~$32 billion returned to shareholders. Noted $1.4B tariff headwind in the quarter. Emphasized R&D-driven opex increases tied to AI.\n\n---\n\n### Data Notes\n- Services revenue: one source cited $26.34B (likely the year-ago comparable), while MacRumors detailed breakdown shows **~$30B** for Q1 FY2026, which is more consistent with Q4 FY2025's $28.8B Services figure.\n- The quarter delivered all-time records for: total revenue, EPS, iPhone revenue, and Services revenue.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Apple Reports Record-Setting 1Q 2026 Results — MacRumors](https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/29/apple-1q-2026-earnings/)\n- [Apple reports first quarter results — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple beats Wall Street expectations — The Desk](https://thedesk.net/2026/01/apple-fiscal-q1-2026-earnings-report/)\n- [Apple Q4 2025: Record $102.5B Revenue — The Acquirer's Multiple](https://acquirersmultiple.com/2025/11/apple-q4-2025-record-102-5b-revenue-surging-services-and-ai-powered-future/)\n- [Apple AAPL Q1 2026 Earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)" ;
