# === finding-23ca1654-97bb-4524-a3d2-4a0114a23c93 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-23ca1654-97bb-4524-a3d2-4a0114a23c93> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:08:48.314133Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Google Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:08:48.313960+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is a comprehensive research summary of Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Alphabet / Google Q4 2025 Earnings — Research Summary\n\n**Reporting period:** October–December 2025 | **Announced:** February 4, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n- **Q4 Revenue:** $113.8 billion (+18% YoY) — beat analyst estimates\n- **Full Year 2025:** $402.8 billion total — first time exceeding $400B annually\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Analyst Estimates\n- **Diluted EPS:** $2.82 (+31% YoY)\n- **Analyst estimate:** ~$2.63\n- **Beat by:** ~$0.19 (roughly 7%)\n- **Net Income:** $34.5 billion (+30% YoY)\n- **Operating Income:** $35.9 billion (+16% YoY)\n- **Operating Margin:** 32.0% (flat YoY)\n\n### 3. Google Search Advertising Revenue\n- **Q4 Search & other:** ~$63.1–63.5 billion (+14–17% YoY, from ~$55.8B in Q4 2024)\n- Key growth verticals: retail, finance, and health — \"nearly every major vertical accelerated in Q4\" (Philipp Schindler, CBO)\n- AI Mode queries doubled daily in US; AI Mode sessions are 3× longer than traditional searches\n\n### 4. YouTube Advertising Revenue\n- **Q4 YouTube ads:** $11.38 billion (+9% YoY)\n- **Missed** analyst expectations of ~$11.84 billion\n- **Annual milestone:** YouTube surpassed $60 billion in combined ads + subscriptions for the first time in 2025\n- **Paid subscriptions:** 325 million across consumer services\n\n### 5. Google Cloud Revenue & Profitability\n- **Q4 Cloud Revenue:** $17.7 billion (+48% YoY) — significant beat\n- **Annual run rate:** Exceeds $70 billion\n- **Cloud Operating Income:** ~$5.3 billion (more than doubled YoY)\n- **Cloud Operating Margin:** Just over 30%\n- **Backlog:** $240 billion (up 55% sequentially, more than doubled YoY)\n- Growth driven by: enterprise AI Infrastructure, AI Solutions, and core GCP products\n\n### 6. Traffic Acquisition Costs (TAC)\n- **Q4 TAC:** ~$15.9–16.6 billion (+~12% YoY)\n- TAC as a percentage of advertising revenues remained **relatively stable** — no margin compression from distribution partner payments\n\n### 7. AI Overviews / Gemini Impact on Search Monetization\n- AI Overviews upgraded to **Gemini 2** (powering best-in-class AI responses at top of search results)\n- Over **250 product launches** in AI Mode and AI Overviews in Q4 alone\n- Management explicitly stated **no cannibalization evidence**: *\"Overall, some of it is what we see as a growth opportunity, and we haven't seen any evidence of cannibalization there.\"* — Sundar Pichai\n- One in six AI Mode queries uses **non-text formats** (multimodal growth)\n- **Gemini app MAUs:** 750 million (up from 650M in Q3)\n- Gemini API throughput: exceeds 10 billion tokens/minute\n- Gemini serving unit costs declined **78%** throughout 2025\n\n### 8. Forward Guidance & Capital Expenditure\n- **FY 2026 CapEx guidance:** $175–185 billion (nearly **doubling** 2025 spend)\n  - ~60% toward servers/machines\n  - ~40% toward long-duration assets (data centers, networking)\n- Just over 50% of ML compute expected to serve the Cloud business; remainder supports Search, YouTube, and consumer products\n- Supply constraints in AI infrastructure expected to persist through 2026\n\n### 9. Key Management Commentary on AI Strategy\n- **AI agent code generation:** ~50% of Google's internal code is now written by AI agents\n- **Enterprise AI momentum:** Cloud backlog acceleration ($240B) driven by AI workload commitments\n- **Gemini ecosystem:** Positioned as unified AI layer across Search, Cloud, Workspace, and Android\n- **Sundar Pichai framing:** AI investments are compounding — cost efficiency (78% serving cost reduction) enables scale, which funds further R&D and infrastructure\n\n---\n\n### Quick-Reference Table\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | YoY Change | vs. Estimate |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Total Revenue | $113.8B | +18% | Beat |\n| Diluted EPS | $2.82 | +31% | Beat ($2.63 est.) |\n| Net Income | $34.5B | +30% | Beat |\n| Google Search | ~$63.1–63.5B | +14–17% | Beat |\n| YouTube Ads | $11.38B | +9% | Miss ($11.84B est.) |\n| Google Cloud | $17.7B | +48% | Beat |\n| Cloud Op. Margin | ~30%+ | Doubled | Strong |\n| TAC | ~$15.9–16.6B | +12% | Stable % of revenue |\n| 2026 CapEx Guide | $175–185B | ~2× 2025 | Aggressive |\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Alphabet (GOOGL) Q4 2025 earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Alphabet reports Q4 2025 revenue of $113.8 billion — 9to5Google](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-q4-2025-earnings/)\n- [Alphabet earnings, Q4 2025: CEO's remarks — Google Blog](https://blog.google/company-news/inside-google/message-ceo/alphabet-earnings-q4-2025/)\n- [Alphabet Investor Relations — Q4 2025 Earnings](https://abc.xyz/investor/news/news-details/2026/Alphabet-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-2025-and-Fiscal-Year-Results-2026-KEvZIMKBLS/default.aspx)\n- [Alphabet Q4 FY 2025 Highlights — Futurum Group](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/alphabet-q4-fy-2025-highlights-cloud-acceleration-and-enterprise-ai-momentum/)\n- [Alphabet advertising revenues climb 14%, Gemini reaches 750M users — PPC Land](https://ppc.land/alphabet-advertising-revenues-climb-14-as-gemini-app-reaches-750-million-users/)\n- [Alphabet Q4 Highlights: Cloud +48%, YouTube tops $60B — Finviz](https://finviz.com/news/300252/alphabet-q4-highlights-google-cloud-revenue-up-48-youtube-tops-60-billion-for-2025)\n- [Official SEC Filing — Q4 2025 Earnings Release](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1652044/000165204426000012/googexhibit991q42025.htm)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "4df6cb55-d604-4bbc-8797-8c354e66db53" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a comprehensive research summary of Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Alphabet / Google Q4 2025 Earnings — Research Summary\n\n**Reporting period:** October–December 2025 | **Announced:** February 4, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n- **Q4 Revenue:** $113.8 billion (+18% YoY) — beat analyst estimates\n- **Full Year 2025:** $402.8 billion total — first time exceeding $400B annually\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Analyst Estimates\n- **Diluted EPS:** $2.82 (+31% YoY)\n- **Analyst estimate:** ~$2.63\n- **Beat by:** ~$0.19 (roughly 7%)\n- **Net Income:** $34.5 billion (+30% YoY)\n- **Operating Income:** $35.9 billion (+16% YoY)\n- **Operating Margin:** 32.0% (flat YoY)\n\n### 3. Google Search Advertising Revenue\n- **Q4 Search & other:** ~$63.1–63.5 billion (+14–17% YoY, from ~$55.8B in Q4 2024)\n- Key growth verticals: retail, finance, and health — \"nearly every major vertical accelerated in Q4\" (Philipp Schindler, CBO)\n- AI Mode queries doubled daily in US; AI Mode sessions are 3× longer than traditional searches\n\n### 4. YouTube Advertising Revenue\n- **Q4 YouTube ads:** $11.38 billion (+9% YoY)\n- **Missed** analyst expectations of ~$11.84 billion\n- **Annual milestone:** YouTube surpassed $60 billion in combined ads + subscriptions for the first time in 2025\n- **Paid subscriptions:** 325 million across consumer services\n\n### 5. Google Cloud Revenue & Profitability\n- **Q4 Cloud Revenue:** $17.7 billion (+48% YoY) — significant beat\n- **Annual run rate:** Exceeds $70 billion\n- **Cloud Operating Income:** ~$5.3 billion (more than doubled YoY)\n- **Cloud Operating Margin:** Just over 30%\n- **Backlog:** $240 billion (up 55% sequentially, more than doubled YoY)\n- Growth driven by: enterprise AI Infrastructure, AI Solutions, and core GCP products\n\n### 6. Traffic Acquisition Costs (TAC)\n- **Q4 TAC:** ~$15.9–16.6 billion (+~12% YoY)\n- TAC as a percentage of advertising revenues remained **relatively stable** — no margin compression from distribution partner payments\n\n### 7. AI Overviews / Gemini Impact on Search Monetization\n- AI Overviews upgraded to **Gemini 2** (powering best-in-class AI responses at top of search results)\n- Over **250 product launches** in AI Mode and AI Overviews in Q4 alone\n- Management explicitly stated **no cannibalization evidence**: *\"Overall, some of it is what we see as a growth opportunity, and we haven't seen any evidence of cannibalization there.\"* — Sundar Pichai\n- One in six AI Mode queries uses **non-text formats** (multimodal growth)\n- **Gemini app MAUs:** 750 million (up from 650M in Q3)\n- Gemini API throughput: exceeds 10 billion tokens/minute\n- Gemini serving unit costs declined **78%** throughout 2025\n\n### 8. Forward Guidance & Capital Expenditure\n- **FY 2026 CapEx guidance:** $175–185 billion (nearly **doubling** 2025 spend)\n  - ~60% toward servers/machines\n  - ~40% toward long-duration assets (data centers, networking)\n- Just over 50% of ML compute expected to serve the Cloud business; remainder supports Search, YouTube, and consumer products\n- Supply constraints in AI infrastructure expected to persist through 2026\n\n### 9. Key Management Commentary on AI Strategy\n- **AI agent code generation:** ~50% of Google's internal code is now written by AI agents\n- **Enterprise AI momentum:** Cloud backlog acceleration ($240B) driven by AI workload commitments\n- **Gemini ecosystem:** Positioned as unified AI layer across Search, Cloud, Workspace, and Android\n- **Sundar Pichai framing:** AI investments are compounding — cost efficiency (78% serving cost reduction) enables scale, which funds further R&D and infrastructure\n\n---\n\n### Quick-Reference Table\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | YoY Change | vs. Estimate |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Total Revenue | $113.8B | +18% | Beat |\n| Diluted EPS | $2.82 | +31% | Beat ($2.63 est.) |\n| Net Income | $34.5B | +30% | Beat |\n| Google Search | ~$63.1–63.5B | +14–17% | Beat |\n| YouTube Ads | $11.38B | +9% | Miss ($11.84B est.) |\n| Google Cloud | $17.7B | +48% | Beat |\n| Cloud Op. Margin | ~30%+ | Doubled | Strong |\n| TAC | ~$15.9–16.6B | +12% | Stable % of revenue |\n| 2026 CapEx Guide | $175–185B | ~2× 2025 | Aggressive |\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Alphabet (GOOGL) Q4 2025 earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Alphabet reports Q4 2025 revenue of $113.8 billion — 9to5Google](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-q4-2025-earnings/)\n- [Alphabet earnings, Q4 2025: CEO's remarks — Google Blog](https://blog.google/company-news/inside-google/message-ceo/alphabet-earnings-q4-2025/)\n- [Alphabet Investor Relations — Q4 2025 Earnings](https://abc.xyz/investor/news/news-details/2026/Alphabet-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-2025-and-Fiscal-Year-Results-2026-KEvZIMKBLS/default.aspx)\n- [Alphabet Q4 FY 2025 Highlights — Futurum Group](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/alphabet-q4-fy-2025-highlights-cloud-acceleration-and-enterprise-ai-momentum/)\n- [Alphabet advertising revenues climb 14%, Gemini reaches 750M users — PPC Land](https://ppc.land/alphabet-advertising-revenues-climb-14-as-gemini-app-reaches-750-million-users/)\n- [Alphabet Q4 Highlights: Cloud +48%, YouTube tops $60B — Finviz](https://finviz.com/news/300252/alphabet-q4-highlights-google-cloud-revenue-up-48-youtube-tops-60-billion-for-2025)\n- [Official SEC Filing — Q4 2025 Earnings Release](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1652044/000165204426000012/googexhibit991q42025.htm)" ;
