# === finding-6150e0b8-1028-466e-858a-bf0b6ec46934 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-6150e0b8-1028-466e-858a-bf0b6ec46934> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:10:25.147934Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Google Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:10:25.147771+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is a comprehensive summary of the market and sector reaction to Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earnings (reported February 4, 2026):\n\n---\n\n## 1. Alphabet (GOOGL) Stock Price Movement\n\n**Earnings day (Feb 4, 2026):**\n- Initial after-hours reaction: stock plunged **~7.5%**, erasing ~$350B in market cap within minutes\n- Reversed sharply to gain **+4%**, causing ~$800B in market cap to swing back and forth within minutes\n- Closed the following day (Feb 5) **essentially flat** — the beat failed to drive sustained gains\n\n**Key driver of volatility:** CapEx guidance of **$175–185B for 2026** (~double 2025 spending) shocked investors despite the earnings beat. Wall Street had expected ~$116B.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Ad Tech Sector Impact\n\n**Overall ad market backdrop was healthy:**\n- The \"triopoly\" (Google, Meta, Amazon) all posted double-digit YoY ad revenue growth in Q4\n- Meta and Amazon were standouts, each exceeding **20% YoY** growth vs. Google's **13.5%**\n- Google's **share of digital ad revenues is trending slightly downward**, with Meta and Amazon set to gain share through 2027\n\n**YouTube: a specific miss**\n- YouTube ads: **$11.38B** vs. $11.84B expected — a notable shortfall that weighed on sentiment for video ad platforms\n\n**Broader ad-tech names:**\n- **Trade Desk (TTD):** Suffered a **67% stock collapse** in the period — driven more by its own CFO departure, AI disruption fears, and tariff uncertainty than directly by Google's earnings; reported $2.896B revenue in 2025 (+18% YoY, slowing from 26% in 2024)\n- **Snap:** Q4 revenues +10.6% YoY; Dynamic Product Ads up 19% — increasingly a bottom-funnel contender\n- **Reddit:** Emerged as a bright spot with ad revenues up **75% YoY**\n- **Pinterest/TTD:** No direct correlated moves tied specifically to Google's earnings day found\n\n---\n\n## 3. Cloud Sector Reaction\n\nGoogle Cloud was the **standout positive** of the report:\n- Revenue: **$17.7B, +48% YoY** (vs. ~35% expected by analysts — a massive beat)\n- Operating income: **$5.3B** (vs. $3.7B expected; 2.5x year-ago level)\n- Operating margin: **>30%**\n- Backlog: **$240B**, more than doubled YoY; +55% sequentially\n\n**Competitive implications:** Google Cloud's 48% growth outpaced Microsoft Azure for the first time in years, intensifying competition with AWS and Azure. Gemini serving costs fell **78% across 2025**, improving economics for enterprise AI workloads. The cloud beat was seen as validating the massive AI infrastructure spend.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Analyst Reactions on AI Search Monetization\n\n| Analyst / Firm | View |\n|---|---|\n| **Barclays** | Cloud growth \"astonishing\"; metrics justify the 100% capex increase; \"AI story is getting better while Search is accelerating\" |\n| **RBC Capital Markets** (Brad Erickson) | Gemini app momentum + cloud spike are \"plenty good as proof points which warrant the higher spend\" |\n| **DA Davidson** (Gil Luria) | Strong profitability justifies increased spending vs. competitors |\n| **Deutsche Bank** | Alphabet \"stunned the world\" with capex plan but \"with tech in a current state of flux, it's not clear whether that's a good or bad thing\" |\n| **Futurum Group** (Nick Patience) | Quarter demonstrates \"AI translating into commercial traction across Cloud, Search, YouTube, and subscriptions\" |\n\n**Key AI Search finding:** Management confirmed **no cannibalization** of Search from Gemini/AI Overviews — instead, AI Mode is *expanding* query volume including commercial queries. Daily AI Mode queries per user **doubled since launch** in the US. AI Max was adopted by **hundreds of thousands of advertisers**.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Competitive Implications for Ad Tech\n\n- Google's slight ad share erosion signals a **structural shift** — Meta and Amazon are compounding their advantages in performance advertising\n- YouTube's miss raised questions about **competition from TikTok and short-form video** alternatives\n- Google's AI search monetization narrative was **constructive** — advertisers are adopting AI Max at scale, meaning AI Overviews are being successfully commercialized rather than displacing ad revenue\n- The **$240B cloud backlog** (2x YoY) signals Google is locking in enterprise commitments that compete directly with AWS and Azure, with implications for the broader cloud infrastructure investment thesis\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Alphabet (GOOGL) Q4 2025 earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Alphabet shares close flat after earnings beat - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/alphabet-earnings-share-price-google-beat-artifical-intelligence.html)\n- [Google Cloud Revenue Surges 48% - TradingKey](https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261554176-google-goog-googl-stock-q4-earnings-cloud-capex-tradingkey)\n- [Alphabet Q4 FY 2025 Highlights Cloud Acceleration - Futurum Group](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/alphabet-q4-fy-2025-highlights-cloud-acceleration-and-enterprise-ai-momentum/)\n- [Alphabet stock sinks after $180B spending plan - Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/alphabet-2026-spending-forecast-soars-past-wall-street-expectations-as-google-parent-goes-all-in-on-ai-195254701.html)\n- [Live: Q4 2025 Advertising Earnings Tracker - eMarketer](https://www.emarketer.com/content/q4-2025-advertising-earnings-tracker)\n- [The Trade Desk Faces Its Most Important Revenue Test - 24/7 Wall St.](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/02/25/the-trade-desk-faces-its-most-important-revenue-test-after-a-67-collapse/)\n- [Alphabet Earnings Call Transcript - Motley Fool](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "af9fb9c0-28ba-4779-978c-64ba8a34c1b1" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a comprehensive summary of the market and sector reaction to Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earnings (reported February 4, 2026):\n\n---\n\n## 1. Alphabet (GOOGL) Stock Price Movement\n\n**Earnings day (Feb 4, 2026):**\n- Initial after-hours reaction: stock plunged **~7.5%**, erasing ~$350B in market cap within minutes\n- Reversed sharply to gain **+4%**, causing ~$800B in market cap to swing back and forth within minutes\n- Closed the following day (Feb 5) **essentially flat** — the beat failed to drive sustained gains\n\n**Key driver of volatility:** CapEx guidance of **$175–185B for 2026** (~double 2025 spending) shocked investors despite the earnings beat. Wall Street had expected ~$116B.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Ad Tech Sector Impact\n\n**Overall ad market backdrop was healthy:**\n- The \"triopoly\" (Google, Meta, Amazon) all posted double-digit YoY ad revenue growth in Q4\n- Meta and Amazon were standouts, each exceeding **20% YoY** growth vs. Google's **13.5%**\n- Google's **share of digital ad revenues is trending slightly downward**, with Meta and Amazon set to gain share through 2027\n\n**YouTube: a specific miss**\n- YouTube ads: **$11.38B** vs. $11.84B expected — a notable shortfall that weighed on sentiment for video ad platforms\n\n**Broader ad-tech names:**\n- **Trade Desk (TTD):** Suffered a **67% stock collapse** in the period — driven more by its own CFO departure, AI disruption fears, and tariff uncertainty than directly by Google's earnings; reported $2.896B revenue in 2025 (+18% YoY, slowing from 26% in 2024)\n- **Snap:** Q4 revenues +10.6% YoY; Dynamic Product Ads up 19% — increasingly a bottom-funnel contender\n- **Reddit:** Emerged as a bright spot with ad revenues up **75% YoY**\n- **Pinterest/TTD:** No direct correlated moves tied specifically to Google's earnings day found\n\n---\n\n## 3. Cloud Sector Reaction\n\nGoogle Cloud was the **standout positive** of the report:\n- Revenue: **$17.7B, +48% YoY** (vs. ~35% expected by analysts — a massive beat)\n- Operating income: **$5.3B** (vs. $3.7B expected; 2.5x year-ago level)\n- Operating margin: **>30%**\n- Backlog: **$240B**, more than doubled YoY; +55% sequentially\n\n**Competitive implications:** Google Cloud's 48% growth outpaced Microsoft Azure for the first time in years, intensifying competition with AWS and Azure. Gemini serving costs fell **78% across 2025**, improving economics for enterprise AI workloads. The cloud beat was seen as validating the massive AI infrastructure spend.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Analyst Reactions on AI Search Monetization\n\n| Analyst / Firm | View |\n|---|---|\n| **Barclays** | Cloud growth \"astonishing\"; metrics justify the 100% capex increase; \"AI story is getting better while Search is accelerating\" |\n| **RBC Capital Markets** (Brad Erickson) | Gemini app momentum + cloud spike are \"plenty good as proof points which warrant the higher spend\" |\n| **DA Davidson** (Gil Luria) | Strong profitability justifies increased spending vs. competitors |\n| **Deutsche Bank** | Alphabet \"stunned the world\" with capex plan but \"with tech in a current state of flux, it's not clear whether that's a good or bad thing\" |\n| **Futurum Group** (Nick Patience) | Quarter demonstrates \"AI translating into commercial traction across Cloud, Search, YouTube, and subscriptions\" |\n\n**Key AI Search finding:** Management confirmed **no cannibalization** of Search from Gemini/AI Overviews — instead, AI Mode is *expanding* query volume including commercial queries. Daily AI Mode queries per user **doubled since launch** in the US. AI Max was adopted by **hundreds of thousands of advertisers**.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Competitive Implications for Ad Tech\n\n- Google's slight ad share erosion signals a **structural shift** — Meta and Amazon are compounding their advantages in performance advertising\n- YouTube's miss raised questions about **competition from TikTok and short-form video** alternatives\n- Google's AI search monetization narrative was **constructive** — advertisers are adopting AI Max at scale, meaning AI Overviews are being successfully commercialized rather than displacing ad revenue\n- The **$240B cloud backlog** (2x YoY) signals Google is locking in enterprise commitments that compete directly with AWS and Azure, with implications for the broader cloud infrastructure investment thesis\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Alphabet (GOOGL) Q4 2025 earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Alphabet shares close flat after earnings beat - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/alphabet-earnings-share-price-google-beat-artifical-intelligence.html)\n- [Google Cloud Revenue Surges 48% - TradingKey](https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261554176-google-goog-googl-stock-q4-earnings-cloud-capex-tradingkey)\n- [Alphabet Q4 FY 2025 Highlights Cloud Acceleration - Futurum Group](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/alphabet-q4-fy-2025-highlights-cloud-acceleration-and-enterprise-ai-momentum/)\n- [Alphabet stock sinks after $180B spending plan - Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/alphabet-2026-spending-forecast-soars-past-wall-street-expectations-as-google-parent-goes-all-in-on-ai-195254701.html)\n- [Live: Q4 2025 Advertising Earnings Tracker - eMarketer](https://www.emarketer.com/content/q4-2025-advertising-earnings-tracker)\n- [The Trade Desk Faces Its Most Important Revenue Test - 24/7 Wall St.](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/02/25/the-trade-desk-faces-its-most-important-revenue-test-after-a-67-collapse/)\n- [Alphabet Earnings Call Transcript - Motley Fool](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Here is a comprehensive summary of the market and sector reaction to Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earni" ;
	a <https://schema.org/SemanticMemory> .


# === finding-6727505d-952c-4622-a7a4-ce1663f22a4f ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-6727505d-952c-4622-a7a4-ce1663f22a4f> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:03:46.825593Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Apple Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:03:46.825440+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is a comprehensive summary of the market reaction to Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings, reported January 29, 2026.\n\n---\n\n## Apple Q1 FY2026 Earnings — Market & Sector Reaction\n\n### 1. Stock Price Movement\n\n| Timeframe | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| Pre-report (Jan 2026) | AAPL down ~4–5% YTD from all-time high of $288.62 |\n| After-hours Jan 29 | Surged **+6%** immediately after the beat |\n| Jan 30 session | Fell **-1.9%** — classic \"sell the news\" reaction; closed ~$259.51 (+0.48% net) |\n| YTD at reporting | Down **-4.23%** despite the in-session recovery |\n\nThe muted post-earnings close despite a major beat reflected broader investor anxiety about \"priced for perfection\" big-tech valuations and AI monetization skepticism.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Analyst Upgrades / Downgrades\n\n**Post-earnings upgrades / price target raises:**\n- **JP Morgan** — target raised to **$325** (from $315 pre-earnings), citing iPhone and services outperformance\n- **Oppenheimer** (Samik Chatterjee) — target raised to **$340** (from $325)\n- **Evercore** (Amit Daryanani) — reaffirmed **Buy**, $330 target\n- **Morningstar** — raised fair value estimate to **$260**\n\n**Pre-earnings downgrade (context):**\n- **Raymond James** (Jan 2, 2026) — downgraded to **Neutral**, citing stretched valuation and limited near-term upside; stock had dropped ~7% from its December peak around this period\n\n---\n\n### 3. Impact on Apple Supplier Stocks\n\n| Supplier | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| **TSMC** | Implemented 3–10% price hikes on Apple effective Jan 1, 2026 — strong pricing power signaled; stock viewed positively |\n| **Micron** | Positive — Apple CEO Tim Cook flagged memory as a growing headwind in Q2+, validating Micron's ramp-up; Micron had posted breakout results with memory price increases |\n| **Cirrus Logic** (86% Apple-dependent) | Record November sales but \"Hold\" rating; concerns about slowing smartphone earnings growth |\n| **Skyworks Solutions** | Late-December decline; analysts considered it undervalued |\n\nCook explicitly warned on the earnings call that **memory cost inflation would become a gross margin headwind in Q2 2026**, which was broadly positive for memory chipmakers (Micron, SK Hynix, Samsung).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Broader Tech Sector Impact\n\nApple's beat provided a floor for indices during a volatile earnings week, but the sector was deeply mixed:\n\n- **Nasdaq-100**: Apple's report helped the index recover ground that week\n- **Microsoft**: Fell **-7%** on slowing Azure cloud growth, despite beating earnings — weighed on the sector\n- **Meta**: Surged **+10%** after demonstrating direct AI-to-ad-revenue monetization — contrasted sharply with Apple's muted reaction\n- **Broader narrative**: \"Simply beating the street is no longer enough\" — markets in 2026 demanded proof that AI investment translates to margin expansion, not just hardware cycle tailwinds\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Surprises vs. Consensus\n\n| Metric | Actual | Consensus | Beat |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | $138.4–138.5B | +~4% |\n| EPS | **$2.84** | $2.67–2.68 | +~6% |\n| iPhone revenue | **$85.3B** | ~$80.2B | +~6.4% |\n| Greater China | **$25.53B (+38% YoY)** | Expected ~flat/modest growth | Major upside surprise |\n| Services | **$30.0B** (76.5% gross margin) | ~$29.9B | Slight beat |\n\n**Greatest surprise:** Greater China revenue up 38% YoY to $25.53B — effectively silenced the bear thesis that Huawei was permanently eroding Apple's China share.\n\n**Notable disappointment framing:** Despite record results, the stock's failure to hold its after-hours +6% gain signaled that investors remain skeptical of sustaining momentum without clearer AI revenue proof points.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- [Apple reports first quarter results — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple (AAPL) earnings report Q1 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)\n- [Apple Defies Market Gravity with Record Holiday Earnings — FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-30-apple-defies-market-gravity-with-record-holiday-earnings-amid-s-and-p-500-slump)\n- [Apple Beats Estimates but Shares Dip as Investors Question AI Premium — FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-30-apple-beats-estimates-in-record-q1-2026-but-shares-dip-as-investors-question-big-techs-ai-premium)\n- [JP Morgan reviews Apple's stock price target — 9to5Mac](https://9to5mac.com/2026/01/30/jp-morgan-reviews-apples-stock-price-target-following-q1-2026-earnings/)\n- [Raymond James downgrades Apple, says gains will be hard in 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/raymond-james-downgrades-apple-says-gains-will-be-hard-to-come-by-in-2026.html)\n- [Apple Earnings: Impressive Q4 Lifts Stock — Morningstar](https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/apple-earnings-impressive-q4-lifts-stock-is-it-long-term-growth-play)\n- [Apple Stock Forecast: Did record Q1 2026 earnings lift targets? — Capital.com](https://capital.com/en-int/analysis/apple-stock-price-in-10-years)\n- [Apple — earnings analysis and stock forecast for 2026 — RoboForex](https://roboforex.com/beginners/analytics/forex-forecast/stocks/stocks-forecast-apple-aapl/)\n- [Apple Q1 FY26 Earnings Preview — IndMoney](https://www.indmoney.com/blog/us-stocks/aapl-stock-in-focus-apple-q1-fy26-earnings)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "3beeab94-decc-4452-9ec5-28ad2ff60bbd" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a comprehensive summary of the market reaction to Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings, reported January 29, 2026.\n\n---\n\n## Apple Q1 FY2026 Earnings — Market & Sector Reaction\n\n### 1. Stock Price Movement\n\n| Timeframe | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| Pre-report (Jan 2026) | AAPL down ~4–5% YTD from all-time high of $288.62 |\n| After-hours Jan 29 | Surged **+6%** immediately after the beat |\n| Jan 30 session | Fell **-1.9%** — classic \"sell the news\" reaction; closed ~$259.51 (+0.48% net) |\n| YTD at reporting | Down **-4.23%** despite the in-session recovery |\n\nThe muted post-earnings close despite a major beat reflected broader investor anxiety about \"priced for perfection\" big-tech valuations and AI monetization skepticism.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Analyst Upgrades / Downgrades\n\n**Post-earnings upgrades / price target raises:**\n- **JP Morgan** — target raised to **$325** (from $315 pre-earnings), citing iPhone and services outperformance\n- **Oppenheimer** (Samik Chatterjee) — target raised to **$340** (from $325)\n- **Evercore** (Amit Daryanani) — reaffirmed **Buy**, $330 target\n- **Morningstar** — raised fair value estimate to **$260**\n\n**Pre-earnings downgrade (context):**\n- **Raymond James** (Jan 2, 2026) — downgraded to **Neutral**, citing stretched valuation and limited near-term upside; stock had dropped ~7% from its December peak around this period\n\n---\n\n### 3. Impact on Apple Supplier Stocks\n\n| Supplier | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| **TSMC** | Implemented 3–10% price hikes on Apple effective Jan 1, 2026 — strong pricing power signaled; stock viewed positively |\n| **Micron** | Positive — Apple CEO Tim Cook flagged memory as a growing headwind in Q2+, validating Micron's ramp-up; Micron had posted breakout results with memory price increases |\n| **Cirrus Logic** (86% Apple-dependent) | Record November sales but \"Hold\" rating; concerns about slowing smartphone earnings growth |\n| **Skyworks Solutions** | Late-December decline; analysts considered it undervalued |\n\nCook explicitly warned on the earnings call that **memory cost inflation would become a gross margin headwind in Q2 2026**, which was broadly positive for memory chipmakers (Micron, SK Hynix, Samsung).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Broader Tech Sector Impact\n\nApple's beat provided a floor for indices during a volatile earnings week, but the sector was deeply mixed:\n\n- **Nasdaq-100**: Apple's report helped the index recover ground that week\n- **Microsoft**: Fell **-7%** on slowing Azure cloud growth, despite beating earnings — weighed on the sector\n- **Meta**: Surged **+10%** after demonstrating direct AI-to-ad-revenue monetization — contrasted sharply with Apple's muted reaction\n- **Broader narrative**: \"Simply beating the street is no longer enough\" — markets in 2026 demanded proof that AI investment translates to margin expansion, not just hardware cycle tailwinds\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Surprises vs. Consensus\n\n| Metric | Actual | Consensus | Beat |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | $138.4–138.5B | +~4% |\n| EPS | **$2.84** | $2.67–2.68 | +~6% |\n| iPhone revenue | **$85.3B** | ~$80.2B | +~6.4% |\n| Greater China | **$25.53B (+38% YoY)** | Expected ~flat/modest growth | Major upside surprise |\n| Services | **$30.0B** (76.5% gross margin) | ~$29.9B | Slight beat |\n\n**Greatest surprise:** Greater China revenue up 38% YoY to $25.53B — effectively silenced the bear thesis that Huawei was permanently eroding Apple's China share.\n\n**Notable disappointment framing:** Despite record results, the stock's failure to hold its after-hours +6% gain signaled that investors remain skeptical of sustaining momentum without clearer AI revenue proof points.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- [Apple reports first quarter results — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple (AAPL) earnings report Q1 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)\n- [Apple Defies Market Gravity with Record Holiday Earnings — FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-30-apple-defies-market-gravity-with-record-holiday-earnings-amid-s-and-p-500-slump)\n- [Apple Beats Estimates but Shares Dip as Investors Question AI Premium — FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-30-apple-beats-estimates-in-record-q1-2026-but-shares-dip-as-investors-question-big-techs-ai-premium)\n- [JP Morgan reviews Apple's stock price target — 9to5Mac](https://9to5mac.com/2026/01/30/jp-morgan-reviews-apples-stock-price-target-following-q1-2026-earnings/)\n- [Raymond James downgrades Apple, says gains will be hard in 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/raymond-james-downgrades-apple-says-gains-will-be-hard-to-come-by-in-2026.html)\n- [Apple Earnings: Impressive Q4 Lifts Stock — Morningstar](https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/apple-earnings-impressive-q4-lifts-stock-is-it-long-term-growth-play)\n- [Apple Stock Forecast: Did record Q1 2026 earnings lift targets? — Capital.com](https://capital.com/en-int/analysis/apple-stock-price-in-10-years)\n- [Apple — earnings analysis and stock forecast for 2026 — RoboForex](https://roboforex.com/beginners/analytics/forex-forecast/stocks/stocks-forecast-apple-aapl/)\n- [Apple Q1 FY26 Earnings Preview — IndMoney](https://www.indmoney.com/blog/us-stocks/aapl-stock-in-focus-apple-q1-fy26-earnings)" ;
