# === finding-6a890b53-143c-48e7-bb48-db7ebbc7b908 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-6a890b53-143c-48e7-bb48-db7ebbc7b908> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:01:00.323234Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Cloud Sector Impact\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "ad1c0b95-d5b5-4b81-8bdc-47c8640c8942" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:01:00.323052+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "## Q4 2025 Cloud Computing Earnings: Sector Impact Report\n\n---\n\n### 1. Cloud Growth Rates — Big Three\n\n| Provider | Revenue | Growth | Key Beat |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **AWS** | $35.58B | +24% YoY | Fastest growth in 13 quarters; beat est. $34.93B |\n| **Google Cloud** | $17.7B | +48% YoY | Fastest growth among Big Three |\n| **Azure** | ~$29.9B segment | +39% YoY | Beat est. 34–35%; AI contributed ~16 pp |\n\n- **Reported dates:** Google Cloud (Feb 4), AWS (Feb 5), Microsoft FY Q2 2026 (Jan 29)\n- Total cloud infrastructure spend Q4 2025: **$119B**, up 30% YoY — 9th consecutive quarter of accelerating growth\n\n---\n\n### 2. Market Share Shifts\n\n| Provider | Q4 2025 Share | YoY Change |\n|---|---|---|\n| AWS | ~28% | -2 pp |\n| Azure | ~21% | +1 pp |\n| Google Cloud | ~14% | +2 pp |\n\nGoogle Cloud was the biggest share gainer; AWS ceded ground despite strong absolute revenue.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Cloud-Adjacent Stock Reactions\n\n- **Cloudflare (NET):** +~80% in 2025 — edge/AI inference positioning validated\n- **MongoDB (MDB):** +~70% in 2025 — Atlas AI positioning; BofA flagged as top rebound pick\n- **Snowflake (SNOW):** +~45–50% in 2025 — product revenue re-accelerated to 29–32% YoY\n- **Datadog (DDOG):** Roughly flat in 2025 — observability solid but no breakout\n- Early Jan 2026 saw a dip (WCLD -3.3%, CLOU -2.5%) on yield fears before hyperscaler beats revived sentiment\n\n---\n\n### 4. AI-Cloud Revenue Attribution\n\n- **Azure:** AI contributed **~16 percentage points** of 39% growth (up from ~9 pp a year prior); targeting $25B AI revenue by end of FY2026\n- **AWS:** GenAI at a \"multi-billion-dollar run rate\" with triple-digit growth; custom AI chips (Trainium) surpassed **$10B run rate**\n- **Google Cloud:** GenAI revenue grew **>200% YoY** in Q3 2025; Vertex AI/Gemini cited as primary Q4 driver\n- Cross-sector: AI represented ~36% of all cloud workloads; GenAI driving ~half of new cloud market growth\n\n---\n\n### 5. Capital Expenditure\n\n| Company | Q4 Capex | Full Year 2025 | 2026 Guidance |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Amazon | $26.3B | **$131.8B** | **$200B** (consensus was $146B — shocked Wall Street) |\n| Alphabet | $27.9B | **$91.4B** | **$175–185B** |\n| Microsoft | ~$30B+ | **$88.7B** | Growing, more GPU/CPU mix |\n\n- **Combined FY2025 capex (MSFT + AMZN + GOOGL): ~$312B**\n- **Combined 2026 guidance (Big 4 incl. Meta): $635–690B**, ~75% earmarked for AI infrastructure\n- Amazon's 2026 guidance was the biggest shock — 36% above consensus\n\n---\n\n### 6. Enterprise Spending Signals\n\n- Contract backlogs: AWS **$244B** (+40% YoY), Google Cloud **$240B** (doubled YoY, +55% sequentially)\n- Amazon CFO flagged non-AI workloads accelerating too — adoption is broad-based\n- Microsoft flagged \"capacity constrained through first half of fiscal year\" — demand exceeding supply\n- Shift from AI experimentation → **production deployment** confirmed across all three earnings calls\n\n---\n\n### 7. Cloud ETF Performance\n\n- **Jan 2, 2026:** WCLD -3.3%, CLOU -2.5% on yield spike\n- **YTD through pre-earnings (early Feb 2026):** WCLD down ~-19.6%\n- Hyperscaler beats (AWS +24%, Google Cloud +48%) acted as positive catalysts in February, arresting the selloff\n- Full year 2025: both ETFs mildly negative (~-5 to -6%) as rate headwinds offset strong fundamentals\n\n---\n\n### 8. 2026 Forward Outlook\n\n**Run rates entering 2026:**\n- AWS: $142B annualized (+24%); Google Cloud: $70B+ annualized (+48%); Azure: $75B+ annualized (+37–39%)\n- Combined Big Three annual run rate approaching **$290B**\n- Total cloud market projected to grow from ~$860B (2025) to **$1.04T in 2026**\n\n**Consensus themes:**\n1. AI is the primary engine, transitioning to production-scale deployments\n2. Capacity race — $635–690B capex signals multi-year supply build\n3. Google Cloud fastest-growing; Azure narrowing gap with AWS\n4. SaaS layer expected to recover (Snowflake, MongoDB, Datadog) as AI demand flows downstream\n5. Contract backlogs provide high revenue visibility through 2026–2027\n\n**Key risks:** Amazon projected to turn FCF-negative in 2026 (capex exceeding operating cash flows); Alphabet's capex guidance initially spooked markets; GPU/power supply constraints limiting near-term revenue conversion." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "54d0a679-812b-43b3-99eb-d0094bdb232d" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "## Q4 2025 Cloud Computing Earnings: Sector Impact Report\n\n---\n\n### 1. Cloud Growth Rates — Big Three\n\n| Provider | Revenue | Growth | Key Beat |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **AWS** | $35.58B | +24% YoY | Fastest growth in 13 quarters; beat est. $34.93B |\n| **Google Cloud** | $17.7B | +48% YoY | Fastest growth among Big Three |\n| **Azure** | ~$29.9B segment | +39% YoY | Beat est. 34–35%; AI contributed ~16 pp |\n\n- **Reported dates:** Google Cloud (Feb 4), AWS (Feb 5), Microsoft FY Q2 2026 (Jan 29)\n- Total cloud infrastructure spend Q4 2025: **$119B**, up 30% YoY — 9th consecutive quarter of accelerating growth\n\n---\n\n### 2. Market Share Shifts\n\n| Provider | Q4 2025 Share | YoY Change |\n|---|---|---|\n| AWS | ~28% | -2 pp |\n| Azure | ~21% | +1 pp |\n| Google Cloud | ~14% | +2 pp |\n\nGoogle Cloud was the biggest share gainer; AWS ceded ground despite strong absolute revenue.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Cloud-Adjacent Stock Reactions\n\n- **Cloudflare (NET):** +~80% in 2025 — edge/AI inference positioning validated\n- **MongoDB (MDB):** +~70% in 2025 — Atlas AI positioning; BofA flagged as top rebound pick\n- **Snowflake (SNOW):** +~45–50% in 2025 — product revenue re-accelerated to 29–32% YoY\n- **Datadog (DDOG):** Roughly flat in 2025 — observability solid but no breakout\n- Early Jan 2026 saw a dip (WCLD -3.3%, CLOU -2.5%) on yield fears before hyperscaler beats revived sentiment\n\n---\n\n### 4. AI-Cloud Revenue Attribution\n\n- **Azure:** AI contributed **~16 percentage points** of 39% growth (up from ~9 pp a year prior); targeting $25B AI revenue by end of FY2026\n- **AWS:** GenAI at a \"multi-billion-dollar run rate\" with triple-digit growth; custom AI chips (Trainium) surpassed **$10B run rate**\n- **Google Cloud:** GenAI revenue grew **>200% YoY** in Q3 2025; Vertex AI/Gemini cited as primary Q4 driver\n- Cross-sector: AI represented ~36% of all cloud workloads; GenAI driving ~half of new cloud market growth\n\n---\n\n### 5. Capital Expenditure\n\n| Company | Q4 Capex | Full Year 2025 | 2026 Guidance |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Amazon | $26.3B | **$131.8B** | **$200B** (consensus was $146B — shocked Wall Street) |\n| Alphabet | $27.9B | **$91.4B** | **$175–185B** |\n| Microsoft | ~$30B+ | **$88.7B** | Growing, more GPU/CPU mix |\n\n- **Combined FY2025 capex (MSFT + AMZN + GOOGL): ~$312B**\n- **Combined 2026 guidance (Big 4 incl. Meta): $635–690B**, ~75% earmarked for AI infrastructure\n- Amazon's 2026 guidance was the biggest shock — 36% above consensus\n\n---\n\n### 6. Enterprise Spending Signals\n\n- Contract backlogs: AWS **$244B** (+40% YoY), Google Cloud **$240B** (doubled YoY, +55% sequentially)\n- Amazon CFO flagged non-AI workloads accelerating too — adoption is broad-based\n- Microsoft flagged \"capacity constrained through first half of fiscal year\" — demand exceeding supply\n- Shift from AI experimentation → **production deployment** confirmed across all three earnings calls\n\n---\n\n### 7. Cloud ETF Performance\n\n- **Jan 2, 2026:** WCLD -3.3%, CLOU -2.5% on yield spike\n- **YTD through pre-earnings (early Feb 2026):** WCLD down ~-19.6%\n- Hyperscaler beats (AWS +24%, Google Cloud +48%) acted as positive catalysts in February, arresting the selloff\n- Full year 2025: both ETFs mildly negative (~-5 to -6%) as rate headwinds offset strong fundamentals\n\n---\n\n### 8. 2026 Forward Outlook\n\n**Run rates entering 2026:**\n- AWS: $142B annualized (+24%); Google Cloud: $70B+ annualized (+48%); Azure: $75B+ annualized (+37–39%)\n- Combined Big Three annual run rate approaching **$290B**\n- Total cloud market projected to grow from ~$860B (2025) to **$1.04T in 2026**\n\n**Consensus themes:**\n1. AI is the primary engine, transitioning to production-scale deployments\n2. Capacity race — $635–690B capex signals multi-year supply build\n3. Google Cloud fastest-growing; Azure narrowing gap with AWS\n4. SaaS layer expected to recover (Snowflake, MongoDB, Datadog) as AI demand flows downstream\n5. Contract backlogs provide high revenue visibility through 2026–2027\n\n**Key risks:** Amazon projected to turn FCF-negative in 2026 (capex exceeding operating cash flows); Alphabet's capex guidance initially spooked markets; GPU/power supply constraints limiting near-term revenue conversion." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "## Q4 2025 Cloud Computing Earnings: Sector Impact Report\n\n---\n\n### 1. Cloud Growth Rates — Big Th" ;
	a <https://schema.org/SemanticMemory> .


# === finding-73be4d15-e1b6-4843-bc72-6273c7a97008 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-73be4d15-e1b6-4843-bc72-6273c7a97008> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:24:36.795408Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Company Summaries\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
