	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Created `analysis/sectors/semiconductors.md`. The report covers all required sections with specific data points sourced from the company summaries:\n\n- **Executive Summary** — frames the combined ~$220B 2025 / ~$255B+ 2026 hyperscaler CapEx as the defining semiconductor demand signal\n- **AI Chip Demand Signals** — table with per-company CapEx figures, plus detailed custom vs. merchant silicon narrative (AMZN's Trainium at 25–30% of AWS AI compute, GOOGL TPU v5p, MSFT's full NVIDIA dependency)\n- **Apple Supply Chain Effects** — iPhone 17 / A19 on TSMC 3nm+, TSMC +2.1%, AVGO +1.4%, SWKS/QRVO mild positive revisions\n- **Cloud Infrastructure Chip Demand** — GPU, custom ASIC, networking, and HBM implications from combined CapEx\n- **Key Stock Movements** — table with 9 rows covering NVDA (+3.1%, +1.8%, +1.7%), AMD (+2.4%), AVGO (+1.4%, +2.3%), TSMC (+2.1%), and SWKS/QRVO\n- **SOX Index Performance** — trend narrative across all four earnings catalysts\n- **Outlook** — four positive catalysts and four risks (custom silicon displacement, CapEx digestion, export controls, TSMC concentration)\n- **Sources** — all primary company filings, analyst notes, and supplemental data" ;
