# === finding-c6323996-2eaa-48df-80a6-06460b2a667d ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-c6323996-2eaa-48df-80a6-06460b2a667d> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-24T23:51:16.546393Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "ad1c0b95-d5b5-4b81-8bdc-47c8640c8942" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-24T23:51:16.546222+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is the comprehensive summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n# Amazon Q4 2025 (Oct–Dec 2025) Earnings Summary\n\n**Report Date:** February 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 1. Financial Results\n\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|----------|-------------|\n| Revenue | $213.4B | $211.5B | Beat (+$1.9B) |\n| EPS (diluted) | $1.95 | ~$1.97 | Slight miss |\n| Operating Income | $25.0B | — | — |\n| Net Income | $21.2B (+6% YoY) | — | — |\n| Operating Margin | 11.7% | — | +40 bps YoY |\n\n**Full Year 2025:** Revenue $716.9B (+12% YoY); Operating Income $80.0B (+17% YoY); Net Income $77.7B (+31% YoY); Diluted EPS $7.17 (+30% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Segment Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth | Notes |\n|---------|---------|------------|-------|\n| North America | $127.1B | +10% | — |\n| International | $50.7B | +17% (+11% constant currency) | FX tailwind of ~$2.8B |\n| **AWS** | **$35.6B** | **+24%** | **Fastest growth in 13 quarters** |\n\n**AWS Operating Income:** $12.47B (vs. $11.91B consensus — beat)  \nAWS margin was 35.4% TTM (down from 37.0% due to reversal to 5-year depreciation policy)  \nAWS contributes **57% of total operating income**  \nAWS annualized run rate: ~$142B  \nAWS order backlog: $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n**Advertising Revenue:** $21.3B (+22% YoY) — Prime Video ads now in 16 countries, 315M average audience\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Highlights\n\n- **AWS vs. Cloud Peers (Q4 2025):**\n  - AWS: +24% YoY (fastest in 13 quarters)\n  - Azure: ~+25% YoY\n  - Google Cloud: ~+28% YoY\n  - Market share: AWS ~28%, Azure ~21%, GCP ~14%\n  - Google Cloud gained the most share YoY; AWS slipped ~2 pts\n- **AWS Custom Silicon:** Graviton/Trainium chips exceeding $10B annualized run rate at triple-digit growth\n- **Bedrock (AI platform):** Multi-billion-dollar annualized revenue; customer spend +60% QoQ\n- **Capacity constrained:** Management noted AWS is \"capacity constrained for the next couple of years\"\n- Added 1+ gigawatt of new capacity in Q4\n- FY2025 CapEx: $132B (+59% YoY) — Q4 CapEx alone was $39.5B (+42% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Forward Guidance\n\n**Q1 2026:**\n| Metric | Guidance | Consensus |\n|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Revenue | $173.5B–$178.5B | $175.5B |\n| Operating Income | $16.5B–$21.5B | $22.2B |\n\nThe operating income guidance midpoint ($19.0B) **missed consensus of $22.2B** — this was the primary driver of the stock selloff.\n\n**FY2026 CapEx:** ~$200B (predominantly AWS and AI infrastructure), up from $132B in FY2025\n\n---\n\n## 5. Stock Reaction\n\n- **Pre-earnings (Feb 4):** ~$232.99\n- **Post-earnings (Feb 6):** ~$210.32\n- **Move:** ~-$22.67/share (~**-9.7%**)\n- **Driver:** Revenue beat and EPS near-inline were overshadowed by the Q1 operating income guidance miss ($16.5B–$21.5B vs. $22.2B consensus) and the massive $200B capex plan raising near-term margin concern\n\n---\n\n## 6. Analyst Commentary\n\n- **Consensus:** 38 analysts, average price target ~$286.87 — broadly bullish, implying ~34%+ upside from post-earnings levels\n- **Argus Research:** Highest target at $325 (issued Feb 6, 2026) — bullish on AWS AI monetization\n- **Wells Fargo / Citigroup:** Maintained/raised targets around $291 (Feb 6–23, 2026)\n- **DA Davidson:** Downgraded, cut price target from $300 → $175 (Feb 6) — outlier bear citing capex risk and margin compression\n- **Broad theme:** Bulls see the $200B capex as a multi-year demand signal for AWS; bears worried about near-term free cash flow (-$12B adjusted FCF in FY2025) and margin dilution from infrastructure build-out\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sector Impact\n\n**Cloud peers:**\n- Results reinforced strong cloud/AI infrastructure demand; broadly positive for data center REITs, power companies, and semiconductor suppliers\n- Azure (+25%) and GCP (+28%) both slightly outpaced AWS on growth rate, keeping competitive pressure narrative alive\n\n**E-commerce peers:**\n- Amazon's aggressive logistics investment (regionalized hubs, \"Amazon Now\" near-instant delivery) creates continued competitive pressure on Shopify, eBay, Wayfair, Etsy\n- Mixed read for Shopify: Amazon expanding multi-channel fulfillment creates both competition and partnership opportunities\n\n**Logistics/Delivery (UPS, FedEx):**\n- Net negative signal: Amazon continues in-sourcing shipping, taking high-volume, high-density routes from third-party carriers\n- Partial offset: overall e-commerce volume growth benefits all carriers to some degree\n\n---\n\n**Key Takeaway:** Q4 2025 was operationally strong — revenue beat, AWS acceleration, advertising momentum — but the combination of a Q1 guidance operating income miss and the $200B capex announcement spooked near-term investors, causing a ~10% stock drop despite the underlying business strength.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Amazon IR - Q4 Results Press Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC - Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum Group - Amazon Q4 FY2025 Analysis](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Investing.com - Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-amazons-q4-2025-revenue-beats-forecast-stock-dips-93CH-4489218)\n- [Massive Moats - Q4 2025 Earnings Review](https://massivemoats.substack.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-review)\n- [Nasdaq - AWS vs Azure vs Google Cloud Q4](https://www.nasdaq.com/articles/amazons-aws-vs.-microsofts-azure-vs.-google-cloud:-which-company-won-the-cloud-race-in-q4)\n- [Alpha Spread - Analyst Price Targets](https://www.alphaspread.com/market-news/analyst-ratings/analysts-raise-amazon-price-targets-see-breakout-potential-in-2026)\n- [Digital Commerce 360 - Amazon Q4 2025 Sales](https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/article/amazon-sales/)\n- [Brandwoven - Q4 2025 Marketplace Recap](https://gobrandwoven.com/resources/articles/amazons-q4-2025-earnings-marketplace/)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "ed737a66-817b-4a2e-b84b-6fc6d2a52e7a" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is the comprehensive summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n# Amazon Q4 2025 (Oct–Dec 2025) Earnings Summary\n\n**Report Date:** February 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 1. Financial Results\n\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|----------|-------------|\n| Revenue | $213.4B | $211.5B | Beat (+$1.9B) |\n| EPS (diluted) | $1.95 | ~$1.97 | Slight miss |\n| Operating Income | $25.0B | — | — |\n| Net Income | $21.2B (+6% YoY) | — | — |\n| Operating Margin | 11.7% | — | +40 bps YoY |\n\n**Full Year 2025:** Revenue $716.9B (+12% YoY); Operating Income $80.0B (+17% YoY); Net Income $77.7B (+31% YoY); Diluted EPS $7.17 (+30% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Segment Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth | Notes |\n|---------|---------|------------|-------|\n| North America | $127.1B | +10% | — |\n| International | $50.7B | +17% (+11% constant currency) | FX tailwind of ~$2.8B |\n| **AWS** | **$35.6B** | **+24%** | **Fastest growth in 13 quarters** |\n\n**AWS Operating Income:** $12.47B (vs. $11.91B consensus — beat)  \nAWS margin was 35.4% TTM (down from 37.0% due to reversal to 5-year depreciation policy)  \nAWS contributes **57% of total operating income**  \nAWS annualized run rate: ~$142B  \nAWS order backlog: $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n**Advertising Revenue:** $21.3B (+22% YoY) — Prime Video ads now in 16 countries, 315M average audience\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Highlights\n\n- **AWS vs. Cloud Peers (Q4 2025):**\n  - AWS: +24% YoY (fastest in 13 quarters)\n  - Azure: ~+25% YoY\n  - Google Cloud: ~+28% YoY\n  - Market share: AWS ~28%, Azure ~21%, GCP ~14%\n  - Google Cloud gained the most share YoY; AWS slipped ~2 pts\n- **AWS Custom Silicon:** Graviton/Trainium chips exceeding $10B annualized run rate at triple-digit growth\n- **Bedrock (AI platform):** Multi-billion-dollar annualized revenue; customer spend +60% QoQ\n- **Capacity constrained:** Management noted AWS is \"capacity constrained for the next couple of years\"\n- Added 1+ gigawatt of new capacity in Q4\n- FY2025 CapEx: $132B (+59% YoY) — Q4 CapEx alone was $39.5B (+42% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Forward Guidance\n\n**Q1 2026:**\n| Metric | Guidance | Consensus |\n|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Revenue | $173.5B–$178.5B | $175.5B |\n| Operating Income | $16.5B–$21.5B | $22.2B |\n\nThe operating income guidance midpoint ($19.0B) **missed consensus of $22.2B** — this was the primary driver of the stock selloff.\n\n**FY2026 CapEx:** ~$200B (predominantly AWS and AI infrastructure), up from $132B in FY2025\n\n---\n\n## 5. Stock Reaction\n\n- **Pre-earnings (Feb 4):** ~$232.99\n- **Post-earnings (Feb 6):** ~$210.32\n- **Move:** ~-$22.67/share (~**-9.7%**)\n- **Driver:** Revenue beat and EPS near-inline were overshadowed by the Q1 operating income guidance miss ($16.5B–$21.5B vs. $22.2B consensus) and the massive $200B capex plan raising near-term margin concern\n\n---\n\n## 6. Analyst Commentary\n\n- **Consensus:** 38 analysts, average price target ~$286.87 — broadly bullish, implying ~34%+ upside from post-earnings levels\n- **Argus Research:** Highest target at $325 (issued Feb 6, 2026) — bullish on AWS AI monetization\n- **Wells Fargo / Citigroup:** Maintained/raised targets around $291 (Feb 6–23, 2026)\n- **DA Davidson:** Downgraded, cut price target from $300 → $175 (Feb 6) — outlier bear citing capex risk and margin compression\n- **Broad theme:** Bulls see the $200B capex as a multi-year demand signal for AWS; bears worried about near-term free cash flow (-$12B adjusted FCF in FY2025) and margin dilution from infrastructure build-out\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sector Impact\n\n**Cloud peers:**\n- Results reinforced strong cloud/AI infrastructure demand; broadly positive for data center REITs, power companies, and semiconductor suppliers\n- Azure (+25%) and GCP (+28%) both slightly outpaced AWS on growth rate, keeping competitive pressure narrative alive\n\n**E-commerce peers:**\n- Amazon's aggressive logistics investment (regionalized hubs, \"Amazon Now\" near-instant delivery) creates continued competitive pressure on Shopify, eBay, Wayfair, Etsy\n- Mixed read for Shopify: Amazon expanding multi-channel fulfillment creates both competition and partnership opportunities\n\n**Logistics/Delivery (UPS, FedEx):**\n- Net negative signal: Amazon continues in-sourcing shipping, taking high-volume, high-density routes from third-party carriers\n- Partial offset: overall e-commerce volume growth benefits all carriers to some degree\n\n---\n\n**Key Takeaway:** Q4 2025 was operationally strong — revenue beat, AWS acceleration, advertising momentum — but the combination of a Q1 guidance operating income miss and the $200B capex announcement spooked near-term investors, causing a ~10% stock drop despite the underlying business strength.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Amazon IR - Q4 Results Press Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC - Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum Group - Amazon Q4 FY2025 Analysis](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Investing.com - Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-amazons-q4-2025-revenue-beats-forecast-stock-dips-93CH-4489218)\n- [Massive Moats - Q4 2025 Earnings Review](https://massivemoats.substack.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-review)\n- [Nasdaq - AWS vs Azure vs Google Cloud Q4](https://www.nasdaq.com/articles/amazons-aws-vs.-microsofts-azure-vs.-google-cloud:-which-company-won-the-cloud-race-in-q4)\n- [Alpha Spread - Analyst Price Targets](https://www.alphaspread.com/market-news/analyst-ratings/analysts-raise-amazon-price-targets-see-breakout-potential-in-2026)\n- [Digital Commerce 360 - Amazon Q4 2025 Sales](https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/article/amazon-sales/)\n- [Brandwoven - Q4 2025 Marketplace Recap](https://gobrandwoven.com/resources/articles/amazons-q4-2025-earnings-marketplace/)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Here is the comprehensive summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n# Amazon Q4 2025 (Oct–Dec 20" ;
