	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Created `analysis/sectors/ad-tech.md`. The report covers all requested sections using data drawn directly from the company files:\n\n- **Executive Summary** — combined ad revenue context across all platforms\n- **Digital Advertising Market Health** — data table with all platform Q4 figures, holiday season comparison\n- **Search Advertising Trends** — Google Search +13.9%, AI Overviews monetization parity progress, Microsoft/Bing +21% CC, AI disruption risk framing\n- **Video & Social Advertising** — YouTube $12B (+14.3%), CTV ~34% of YouTube revenue, Shorts RPM gap narrowing, META/SNAP/PINS read-throughs\n- **Retail Media & Commerce Ads** — Amazon Advertising $20.6B crossing $80B run-rate, DSP growth, Prime Video CTV inventory\n- **AI Impact on Advertising** — AI-powered tools improving ROI across all platforms, generative AI creative tools\n- **Privacy & Regulation** — Apple ATT ecosystem adaptation, DOJ/DMA regulatory risks\n- **Key Ad Tech Stock Reactions** — table covering GOOGL, AMZN, META, SNAP, PINS, TTD, ROKU, APP with context\n- **Outlook** — forward indicators including retail media acceleration, CTV growth, macro/AI displacement risks" ;
