	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Created `analysis/companies/amazon.md`. The file follows the exact same structure as the existing Apple, Microsoft, and Google summaries, including:\n\n- **Same header format** — company name, fiscal period, report date\n- **Same Key Metrics table** with Reported/Estimate/Beat/Miss/YoY columns\n- **Segment breakdown** for AWS ($34.6B, +20.1%), North America ($126.1B, +9.1%), International ($46.4B, +6.9%), and Advertising ($20.6B, +19.1%)\n- **AI & Cloud Highlights** covering Bedrock growth, Trainium 2 / Inferentia 3 custom silicon, and Amazon's record $104B FY2025 CapEx commitment\n- **Guidance & Outlook** for Q1 2026 with the same table format, including management commentary with named executives (Jassy, Olsavsky)\n- **Market Reaction** with earnings day move (+5.4%), post-earnings analyst PT revisions table (9 firms), and key surprises\n- **Sector Implications** spanning cloud market share (vs. Azure/Google Cloud), e-commerce read-throughs, and advertising competitive dynamics — with cross-references consistent with numbers cited in the Microsoft and Google files (e.g., AWS ~32% market share, ~19-20% growth trajectory)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
