|\n| **Skyworks Solutions** | Late-December decline; analysts considered it undervalued |\n\nCook explicitly warned on the earnings call that **memory cost inflation would become a gross margin headwind in Q2 2026**, which was broadly positive for memory chipmakers (Micron, SK Hynix, Samsung).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Broader Tech Sector Impact\n\nApple's beat provided a floor for indices during a volatile earnings week, but the sector was deeply mixed:\n\n- **Nasdaq-100**: Apple's report helped the index recover ground that week\n- **Microsoft**: Fell **-7%** on slowing Azure cloud growth, despite beating earnings — weighed on the sector\n- **Meta**: Surged **+10%** after demonstrating direct AI-to-ad-revenue monetization — contrasted sharply with Apple's muted reaction\n- **Broader narrative**: \"Simply beating the street is no longer enough\" — markets in 2026 demanded proof that AI investment translates to margin expansion, not just hardware cycle tailwinds\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Surprises vs. Consensus\n\n| Metric | Actual | Consensus | Beat |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | $138.4–138.5B | +~4% |\n| EPS | **$2.84** | $2.67–2.68 | +~6% |\n| iPhone revenue | **$85.3B** | ~$80.2B | +~6.4% |\n| Greater China | **$25.53B (+38% YoY)** | Expected ~flat/modest growth | Major upside surprise |\n| Services | **$30.0B** (76.5% gross margin) | ~$29.9B | Slight beat |\n\n**Greatest surprise:** Greater China revenue up 38% YoY to $25.53B — effectively silenced the bear thesis that Huawei was permanently eroding Apple's China share.\n\n**Notable disappointment framing:** Despite record results, the stock's failure to hold its after-hours +6% gain signaled that investors remain skeptical of sustaining momentum without clearer AI revenue proof points.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- [Apple reports first quarter results — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple (AAPL) earnings report Q1 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.