rth America retail operating margin expanded to **9.0%** in Q4 (vs. 8.0% a year ago)\n- International retail margin: 2.1% — improving but still thin\n- Retail AI enhancements include \"Rufus\" agentic shopping assistant and unified advertising campaign tools\n\n### 8. AI Services & Custom Silicon (Trainium, Inferentia)\n- **Trainium + Graviton families exceed $10B annualized revenue** with triple-digit YoY AI accelerator growth\n- **Trainium2**: 1.4 million chips deployed; 30–40% more price-performant than comparable GPUs\n  - 500,000+ chips in **Anthropic's Project Rainier** cluster (training next Claude model)\n  - Trainium2 is sold out\n- **Trainium3**: Just launched; up to 40% more price-performant than Trainium2; nearly all 2026 supply expected committed by mid-2026\n- **Amazon Bedrock**: Multi-billion-dollar annualized run rate; **60% QoQ customer spend growth**\n- Bedrock Agent Corp launched for deploying agents securely at scale\n- AWS added **1+ GW of data center capacity in Q4**; deployed more capacity globally in 2025 than any other operator\n- AWS CEO Matt Garman: *\"We will sell every single server and every single bit, and we will wish that we had more\"* — capacity constraints expected through 2027–2028\n\n### 9. Forward Guidance & Capital Expenditure Plans\n**Q1 2026 Guidance:**\n- Net sales: **$173.5B–$178.5B** (consensus was $175.5B — in-line)\n- Operating income: **$16.5B–$21.5B** (midpoint $19B vs. consensus $22.2B — **missed**)\n  - Includes ~$1B incremental YoY cost from Project Kuiper (Leo satellite)\n\n**Capital Expenditure:**\n- 2025 actual capex: **$131.8 billion**\n- **2026 guided capex: ~$200 billion** (+53% YoY) — predominantly AWS/AI\n- Plans to **double power capacity by end of 2027**\n- Reinvesting ~90% of operating cash flow into infrastructure\n- Free cash flow declined to $11.2B due to investment surge\n\n### 10. Key Management Commentary\n- **Andy Jassy (CEO):** *\"Every customer experience that we know of today is going to be reinvented… We are gonna invest aggressively here to be the leaders.\"*\n- Jassy on $200B capex: *\"We expect to invest about $200 billion in capital expenditures across Amazon, but predominantly in AWS because we have very high demand.\"*\n- Jassy on AWS growth: *\"We're growing 24% year-over-year on a $142 billion annualized run rate business. So we're growing at a really unprecedented rate.\"*\n- **Stock reaction**: Shares fell ~5% post-earnings on the $200B capex shock and below-consensus Q1 operating income guidance, despite revenue beat\n- AWS serves more S&P 500 companies as primary cloud provider than competitors combined\n\n---\n\n**Key Takeaway:** Amazon delivered a strong revenue beat with AWS at peak acceleration, but the market focused negatively on the massive $200B 2026 capex commitment and a Q1 operating income guide that came in well below consensus — framing this as a heavy investment cycle quarter.\n\nSources:\n- [Amazon Q4 FY 2025: Revenue Beat, AWS +24% Amid $200B Capex Plan](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [AWS Q4 earnings report 2025 - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/aws-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 slides: Revenue jumps 14%, AWS growth accelerates to 24%](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings: The $200B Infrastructure Mandate](https://www.globaldatacenterhub.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-the-200b)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Review - Massive Moats](https://massivemoats.substack.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-review)\n- [Amazon's Q4 2025 Earnings and 2026 Outlook](https://www.levelheadedinvesting.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-and-2026-outlook)\n- [Recap of Amazon's Q4 2025 Earnings for Marketplace Sellers](https://gobrandwoven.com/resources/articles/amazons-q4-2025-earnings-marketplace/)\n- [Amazon.com Announces Fourth Quarter Results (IR)](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2025/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [Amazon (AMZN) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript - Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-005233025.html)" ;
