	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:21:09.208292+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Created `analysis/companies/google.md` following the same structure and detail level as the Apple and Microsoft summaries. Key highlights in the file:\n\n- **Key Metrics table**: $110.0B revenue (+14% YoY), $2.27 EPS, both beats\n- **Segment Performance**: Search ($61.5B, +13.9%), YouTube ($12.0B, +14.3%), Cloud ($14.9B, +30.7% with 14.1% operating margin), Other Bets ($0.5B revenue / -$1.1B loss)\n- **AI & Search Monetization**: AI Overviews at ~3B daily queries approaching monetization parity, ~$2.5B annualized Cloud AI run-rate, TAC ratio improving to 19.4% (from 21.3%)\n- **Guidance**: $75B 2026 CapEx plan, Q1 2026 revenue $112–115B, Cloud at 26–30%\n- **Market Reaction**: GOOGL +4.6% on earnings day to $221.34, new all-time high; consensus PT raised 15% to ~$248\n- **Sector Implications**: Positive digital ad read-through for Meta/Snap; Cloud competitive positioning vs. AWS (19% growth) and Azure (35% CC)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "723a325b-7e1c-4f4b-a3cb-3e6dfec2fa3f" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Created `analysis/companies/google.md` following the same structure and detail level as the Apple and Microsoft summaries. Key highlights in the file:\n\n- **Key Metrics table**: $110.0B revenue (+14% YoY), $2.27 EPS, both beats\n- **Segment Performance**: Search ($61.5B, +13.9%), YouTube ($12.0B, +14.3%), Cloud ($14.9B, +30.7% with 14.1% operating margin), Other Bets ($0.5B revenue / -$1.1B loss)\n- **AI & Search Monetization**: AI Overviews at ~3B daily queries approaching monetization parity, ~$2.5B annualized Cloud AI run-rate, TAC ratio improving to 19.4% (from 21.3%)\n- **Guidance**: $75B 2026 CapEx plan, Q1 2026 revenue $112–115B, Cloud at 26–30%\n- **Market Reaction**: GOOGL +4.6% on earnings day to $221.34, new all-time high; consensus PT raised 15% to ~$248\n- **Sector Implications**: Positive digital ad read-through for Meta/Snap; Cloud competitive positioning vs. AWS (19% growth) and Azure (35% CC)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[coder] Created `analysis/companies/google.md` following the same structure and detail l" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


# === memory-916cb52a-c79f-4b96-9031-afd882c8d2b8 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-916cb52a-c79f-4b96-9031-afd882c8d2b8> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:37:57.013324Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Sector Impact Reports\",\"Write cloud sector report\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "coder" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:37:57.012621+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Created `analysis/sectors/cloud.md`. The report covers all required sections with specific numbers drawn directly from the company files:\n\n- **Hyperscaler table** includes revenue, growth rates (both reported and constant currency), operating margins, AI contribution in percentage points, CapEx figures, and market share estimates — with a note flagging Azure's Intelligent Cloud vs. standalone Azure reporting distinction\n- **AI-driven cloud revenue** details the per-provider AI contribution trajectory (Azure's 8pp is the highest, up from 3pp two quarters prior; AWS's 3–4pp up from 1.5pp; Google's 4pp up from 2pp)\n- **CapEx arms race** shows the combined $255B+ 2026 commitment with CEO quotes from all three confirming the rationale\n- **Ecosystem stock impacts** covers SNOW, CRM, NOW, ADBE, ORCL, and others with specific price moves where documented\n- **Enterprise spending signals** synthesizes the consistent \"AI additive not substitutive\" theme and multi-year contract dynamics\n- **Market share dynamics** flags the Azure vs. AWS growth rate gap (15pp, widest in the AI era) as the key competitive narrative shift\n- **Outlook** covers guidance figures, custom silicon displacement risk, and the SaaS vendor displacement theme" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "b62d59bf-b215-4d2f-a05f-190bea779b60" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Created `analysis/sectors/cloud.md`. The report covers all required sections with specific numbers drawn directly from the company files:\n\n- **Hyperscaler table** includes revenue, growth rates (both reported and constant currency), operating margins, AI contribution in percentage points, CapEx figures, and market share estimates — with a note flagging Azure's Intelligent Cloud vs. standalone Azure reporting distinction\n- **AI-driven cloud revenue** details the per-provider AI contribution trajectory (Azure's 8pp is the highest, up from 3pp two quarters prior; AWS's 3–4pp up from 1.5pp; Google's 4pp up from 2pp)\n- **CapEx arms race** shows the combined $255B+ 2026 commitment with CEO quotes from all three confirming the rationale\n- **Ecosystem stock impacts** covers SNOW, CRM, NOW, ADBE, ORCL, and others with specific price moves where documented\n- **Enterprise spending signals** synthesizes the consistent \"AI additive not substitutive\" theme and multi-year contract dynamics\n- **Market share dynamics** flags the Azure vs. AWS growth rate gap (15pp, widest in the AI era) as the key competitive narrative shift\n- **Outlook** covers guidance figures, custom silicon displacement risk, and the SaaS vendor displacement theme" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[coder] Created `analysis/sectors/cloud.md`. The report covers all required sections wit" ;
