# === memory-a68453bd-4192-4076-a49e-24333fdc76fe ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-a68453bd-4192-4076-a49e-24333fdc76fe> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-24T23:46:26.444334Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Microsoft Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"Search and analyze Microsoft earnings data\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "ad1c0b95-d5b5-4b81-8bdc-47c8640c8942" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-24T23:46:26.443612+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "I now have comprehensive data. Here is the full compiled research summary:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Earnings — Comprehensive Research Summary\n**Quarter Covered:** October–December 2025 | **Reported:** January 28, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Financial Results\n\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Beat/Miss |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Revenue | $81.3B | $80.3B | **Beat +$1.0B** |\n| Non-GAAP EPS | $4.14 | $3.97 | **Beat +$0.17 (+4.3%)** |\n| GAAP EPS | $5.16 | — | Includes $7.6B OpenAI gain |\n| Operating Income | $38.3B | — | +21% YoY |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.5B | — | +60% YoY* |\n| Net Income (non-GAAP) | $30.9B | — | +23% YoY |\n\n*GAAP net income inflated by **$7.6B one-time gain** from OpenAI investment recapitalization; GAAP EPS up 60% vs non-GAAP up 24%.\n\n**Microsoft Cloud (total):** $51.5B (+26% YoY) — first quarter crossing $50B.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Segment Breakdown\n\n#### Intelligent Cloud — $32.9B (+29% YoY)\n- **Azure & cloud services: +39% YoY (+38% constant currency)** — decelerated from 40% in Q1 FY2026\n- Azure AI services on pace for ~$23.6B annualized revenue\n- Missed \"whisper number\" of ~41% growth\n\n#### Productivity & Business Processes — $34.1B (+16% YoY)\n- Microsoft 365 Commercial cloud: +17%\n- Microsoft 365 Consumer cloud: +29%\n- LinkedIn revenue: +11%\n- Dynamics 365: +19%\n- **Copilot M365:** 15 million paid seats, up **160% YoY**; daily active users up **10x YoY**\n- **GitHub Copilot:** 4.7M paid subscribers, up **75% YoY**\n\n#### More Personal Computing — $14.3B (-3% YoY)\n- Windows OEM/Devices: +1%\n- Xbox content/services: -5%\n- Search & news advertising: +10%\n\n---\n\n### 3. Key Highlights\n\n- **Azure 39% growth** — slight deceleration from 40% prior quarter; supply constrained\n- **Commercial Remaining Performance Obligation:** $625B, up **+110% YoY** — ~45% driven by OpenAI commitments\n- **Microsoft Azure Foundry:** 1,500+ customers; 250+ processing >1 trillion tokens/year\n- **Microsoft Fabric:** $2B+ annual revenue run rate; 31,000+ customers; +60% YoY\n- **Capex: $37.5B** for the quarter (+66% YoY, record level; ~$150B annualized run rate)\n  - ~Two-thirds allocated to \"short-lived assets\" (GPUs: H200, Blackwell B200)\n  - Introduced proprietary **Maia 200 inference chip** to reduce Nvidia dependency\n- Cloud gross margin fell to **67%**, down from 72% five quarters prior\n- 1 gigawatt of new capacity added\n\n---\n\n### 4. Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n\n| Item | Guidance |\n|---|---|\n| Total Revenue | $80.65B – $81.75B (+15–17% YoY) |\n| Azure growth (cc) | **37%–38%** (continued deceleration) |\n| Cloud gross margin | ~65% (down from 67% prior quarter) |\n| Capex FY2026 | ~$99B (full fiscal year estimate) |\n\nManagement confirmed capacity constraints will persist \"until 2026\" (i.e., ongoing). Demand continues to outpace supply.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Stock Reaction\n\n| Date | Event | Move |\n|---|---|---|\n| Jan 28 (after-hours) | Earnings release | -7% extended trading |\n| Jan 29, 2026 | Market open | -12% intraday |\n| Jan 30, 2026 | Close | **-9.99%** (largest single-day drop since March 2020) |\n\n- **~$357–400B in market cap erased** — second-largest single-day value loss in U.S. stock history (after Nvidia's $593B loss in January 2025)\n- Trading volume: 126.5M shares (366% above 3-month average)\n- Stock at ~$433.64 by Jan 30; down **22% from October 2025 all-time high of $555.45**\n- 12-month YTD performance at time of drop: only +7%\n\n---\n\n### 6. Analyst Commentary\n\n**Consensus:** Strong Buy (32 Buy, 2 Hold, 0 Sell as of late January 2026)\n\n**Price Targets:**\n- Range: $500 – $678\n- Median 12-month target: **$628.98** (+41% upside from post-earnings price)\n- 24/7 Wall St. target: $676.36\n\n**Notable reactions:**\n- **Deutsche Bank, Goldman Sachs, UBS, Citi:** All maintained **Buy** ratings\n- **Morgan Stanley:** Maintained **Overweight**; noted 21x FY2027 P/E \"underestimates Microsoft's prospects\"\n- **Wedbush (Dan Ives):** Bullish; called 2026 \"the inflection year for AI and MSFT\"; said market wanted \"less capex and faster monetization\"\n- **RBC Capital Markets (Rishi Jaluria):** Growth expectations \"exceeded analyst estimates\" — bearish near-term on capex\n- **Jim Cramer (CNBC):** \"It's the collapse of software and the ascent of hardware\"\n\n**Key bear concerns:**\n- Capex surging 66% with Azure growth decelerating (ROI question)\n- 45% of $625B backlog from OpenAI raises circular-financing risk\n- Gross margin compression (72% → 67% → guided 65%)\n- Monetization pace lagging infrastructure investment\n\n---\n\n### 7. Sector Impact\n\n**Cloud Competitors:**\n- **Google Cloud (Alphabet):** Growing at **48% YoY** — faster than Azure from smaller base; Alphabet stock +0.67% on earnings day (relative winner)\n- **AWS (Amazon):** Growing ~**21-24% YoY** — Microsoft still dominant on AI-first narrative\n- Alphabet planning **$115B+** capex in 2026; Amazon planning **$200B** capex in 2026\n\n**AI/Semiconductor stocks:**\n- **Nvidia:** Primary beneficiary of Microsoft's capex (H200s, Blackwell B200s); however, Microsoft's Maia 200 chip signals longer-term risk to Nvidia dependency\n- Sector-wide concern: the \"AI capex vs. monetization\" gap is a macro theme across all hyperscalers\n\n**Broader Market:**\n- **Nasdaq Composite:** -2.1% on Jan 29\n- **Software Sector ETF (IGV):** Down >20% from recent highs (bear market territory)\n- Microsoft underperformed Google by ~62 percentage points over the trailing 12 months (7% vs. 69% gains)\n- Meta surged +10% the same week on its own earnings — contrasting investor confidence in Meta's AI monetization vs. Microsoft's heavy-infrastructure model\n\n---\n\n### Summary Assessment\n\nMicrosoft delivered a **solid double beat** on revenue and EPS, but the market punished it for three reasons: (1) Azure growth decelerated to 39% vs. whisper numbers of 41%; (2) capex surged to a record $37.5B with forward guidance implying continued heavy spending; (3) gross margin guidance stepped down to 65%. The result: one of the largest single-day market cap destructions in U.S. history despite a fundamentally strong quarter. Long-term bulls point to the $625B commercial backlog, 160% YoY Copilot seat growth, and a strong analyst consensus (32 Buy) as indicators that the selloff was an overreaction.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [FY26 Q2 Press Release — Microsoft Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [Microsoft Cloud and AI Strength Drives Q2 Results — Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Microsoft Q2 FY2026: Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC — Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [Microsoft Records Second-Largest Value Loss in US History — TradingKey](https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261532135-microsoft-earnings-msft-stocks-drop-tradingkey)\n- [Microsoft MSFT Analysis 2026: The $400 Billion Reality Check — Vocal/Trader](https://vocal.media/trader/microsoft-stock-msft-analysis-2026-the-400-billion-reality-check-that-shook-wall-street)\n- [Microsoft's AI Valuation Crossroads: Deep Dive Q2 2026 — FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-2-9-microsofts-ai-valuation-crossroads-a-deep-dive-into-q2-2026-earnings)\n- [Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Earnings: $81B Quarter — SAM Expert](https://samexpert.com/microsoft-q2-fy2026-earnings-licensing-impact/)\n- [Microsoft Q2 2026 Results — ERP.Today](https://erp.today/microsoft-q2-2026-results-show-ai-cloud-growth-accelerating-as-spending-surges/)\n- [Microsoft MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026 — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Microsoft Stock Price Prediction 2026 — 24/7 Wall St.](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/01/29/microsoft-nasdaq-msft-stock-price-prediction-for-2025-where-will-it-be-in-1-year/)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
