	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is the compiled research on Q4 2025 big tech earnings and their impact on the ad tech sector:\n\n---\n\n## Ad Tech Sector: Q4 2025 Big Tech Earnings Impact\n\n---\n\n### 1. Digital Ad Trends — Big Tech Revenue\n\n#### Google/Alphabet (Q4 2025, reported Feb 4, 2026)\n- **Total ad revenue**: $82.28B (+13.5% YoY)\n- **Google Search**: $63.07B (+17% YoY from $54.03B) — driven by AI Overviews and AI Max campaigns\n- **YouTube Ads**: $11.38B (+9% YoY) — missed analyst estimate of $11.84B\n- **Total Alphabet revenue**: $113.8B (+18% YoY); first time annual revenue exceeded $400B\n- **EPS**: $2.82 vs. $2.63 consensus estimate\n\n#### Amazon (Q4 2025, reported Feb 5, 2026)\n- **Advertising Services**: $21.32B (+23% YoY) — outpaced Google's ad growth rate\n- Added $12B+ of incremental ad revenue in 2025 alone\n- Prime Video ads now in 16 countries; avg ad-supported audience 315M globally (up from 200M in early 2024)\n- Advertising Services = 9.6% of total TTM revenue\n\n#### Microsoft/LinkedIn (Fiscal Q2 2026 = calendar Q4 2025, reported Jan 28, 2026)\n- **Total Microsoft revenue**: $81.3B (+17% YoY)\n- **Search & news advertising** (excl. TAC): +10% YoY\n- **LinkedIn revenue**: +11% YoY driven by Marketing Solutions; video ads +30% YoY\n- Forward guidance: LinkedIn low-double digit revenue growth\n\n#### Apple (Fiscal Q4 2025, reported Oct 30, 2025 — quarter ended Sept 27)\n- **Services revenue**: $28.8B (+15% YoY), all-time record\n- Advertising hit all-time records (not broken out separately within Services)\n- Apple Search Ads now commands ~35% of all iOS app install ad spend (up from 25% in 2021)\n- Total revenue: $102.5B (+8% YoY); first time services overtook iPhone in gross profit contribution (42% vs. 41%)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Ad Tech Sector Stock Reactions\n\n#### Meta (META) — Reported Jan 28, 2026 — **Strong positive signal**\n- **Q4 revenue**: $59.9B (+24% YoY); beat $58.4B consensus\n- **Ad revenue**: $58.1B; impressions +18%, avg price per ad +6%\n- **Full-year 2025 ad revenue**: ~$196B total\n- Stock surged ~9.71% in after-hours to $738.31\n- Interpretation: bullish signal for the broader ad market; AI-powered targeting demonstrably improving performance\n\n#### AppLovin (APP) — Reported ~Feb 12, 2026 — **Beat but stock dipped**\n- **Q4 revenue**: $1.66B (+66% YoY); beat $1.61B estimate\n- **EPS**: $3.24 vs. $2.96 estimate; free cash flow +88% YoY\n- **Full-year 2025 revenue**: $5.48B (+70%)\n- Q1 2026 guidance: $1.745–1.775B revenue; 84% adjusted EBITDA margin maintained\n- Stock fell ~3.32% in aftermarket despite the beat — \"buy the rumor, sell the news\" dynamic; meta threat to mobile gaming ad dominance loomed\n\n#### The Trade Desk (TTD) — Reported Feb 25–26, 2026 — **Major selloff**\n- **Q4 revenue**: $847M (+14% YoY; ~+19% excl. political spend) — beat $841M estimate\n- **Adjusted EBITDA**: $400M at 47% margin\n- **Q1 2026 guidance**: \"at least $678M\" — implied ~10% growth, badly missing $689–696M consensus\n- **Stock crashed 16%+** post-earnings; had already collapsed 67–77% from 2024 highs\n- CEO Jeff Green flagged weakness in CPG and automotive verticals; macro uncertainty not seen in over a decade\n\n#### Snap (SNAP) — Reported Feb 4, 2026 — **Modest growth**\n- **Q4 revenue**: $1.716B (+10% YoY)\n- **Ad revenue**: $1.48B, driven by direct response advertising\n- **Subscribers**: +71% YoY to 24M (Snapchat+)\n- Full-year 2025 revenue: $5.93B (+11% YoY)\n\n#### Pinterest (PINS) — Reported Feb 12, 2026 — **Revenue miss**\n- **Q4 revenue**: $1.32B (+14.3% YoY) — missed $1.33B estimate by ~0.8%\n- Blamed retail ad pullbacks from large clients hit by tariffs and margin pressures\n- **MAUs**: Record 619M (+12% YoY) — 10 consecutive record quarters\n\n---\n\n### 3. AI Impact on Advertising\n\n#### Google\n- **AI Overviews**: Ads integrated into AI Overviews; expanded globally in 2025; testing ads in AI Mode (deeper/complex queries)\n- **AI Max for Search**: Campaigns using AI Max + Smart Bidding Exploration saw avg 18% increase in unique search query categories with conversions and 19% increase in overall conversions\n- **Creative scale**: Gemini generated nearly 70 million creative assets in Q4 2025 alone (3x YoY increase)\n- **Market impact**: Paid CTRs declining but CPCs at a 6-year high as AI Overviews compress above-the-fold paid placement\n\n#### Meta\n- **GEM ranking model**: Doubled GPU training; sequence-learning architecture using longer interaction histories → 3.5% YoY lift in ad clicks on Facebook, 1%+ lift in Instagram conversions\n- **Lattice model**: Consolidated Stories ads → 12% YoY improvement in ads quality\n- **Video generation**: AI-driven creative tools at $10B+ annual run rate, growing ~3x faster than overall ad revenue\n- **Measurement**: Latest attribution models drove 24% increase in incremental conversions\n\n#### AppLovin\n- AXON 2.0 AI engine is the core thesis; 66% revenue growth directly attributed to AI-powered targeting in mobile gaming and e-commerce\n\n---\n\n### 4. Privacy & Regulatory Environment\n\n- **Apple ATT**: Now enforced since iOS 14.5 (2021); continues reshaping mobile ad targeting. User acquisition costs on iOS up 20–30% CPI vs. pre-ATT. Apple Search Ads beneficiary, capturing 35% of iOS install ad spend.\n- **Apple + AdAttributionKit**: April 2025 integration of Apple Search Ads with AdAttributionKit to provide unified cross-network attribution measurement\n- **France vs. Apple**: France's Autorité de la Concurrence (March 2025) preparing fine of up to 10% of Apple's global revenue; may order Apple to **stop enforcing ATT** in France — significant regulatory development for the mobile ad ecosystem\n- **Meta**: ATT constraints mostly absorbed; AI-powered on-platform measurement (Conversions API, Advantage+ suite) has substantially offset signal loss\n- **Trade Desk + Kokai**: TTD's identity resolution and clean room integrations are responses to cookie deprecation pressure; OpenPath growth continued\n\n---\n\n### 5. Forward Outlook: 2026 Ad Spending Projections\n\n| Source | Global 2026 Forecast | U.S. 2026 Forecast |\n|--------|---------------------|---------------------|\n| Dentsu | +6.3%, surpassing $1 trillion for first time | — |\n| MAGNA | Advertising resilient amid economic uncertainty | — |\n| IAB | — | +9.5% YoY (excl. cyclical events: +7.1–7.8%) |\n| S&P Global | Robust | Robust |\n\n**Fastest-growing digital channels (U.S. 2026 IAB forecast):**\n- Social media: **+14.6%**\n- Connected TV: **+13.8%**\n- Commerce media: **+12.1%**\n\n**Key themes driving 2026 outlook:**\n1. **AI is the defining force** — 5 of 6 top advertiser priorities are AI-related (agentic AI, autonomous planning, AI creative generation, AI measurement, AI bidding)\n2. **Commerce media acceleration** — Amazon's ad business growing at 2x the rate of traditional search; retail media networks scaling\n3. **CTV momentum** — Streaming ad tiers from Amazon (Prime Video), Netflix, Disney+ all maturing\n4. **Performance over brand** — Macro uncertainty (tariffs, CPG/auto pullbacks) is accelerating the shift to measurable, ROI-driven spending\n\n---\n\n### Summary: Big Tech → Ad Tech Read-Through\n\n| Signal | Impact |\n|--------|--------|\n| Google Search +17% | Confirmed search demand robust; AI not cannibalizing revenue yet |\n| Amazon Ads +23% | Commerce/retail media is the fastest-growing segment; structurally taking share from Google |\n| Meta +24% | AI-powered targeting working; advertisers getting better ROI, increasing spend |\n| Microsoft/LinkedIn +11% | B2B ad market healthy; video ads accelerating |\n| TTD guidance miss | Independent DSPs under pressure; fragmentation concerns; buyers consolidating into walled gardens |\n| AppLovin +66% | AI-native mobile ad platforms winning; existential threat to legacy programmatic |\n| Snap +10% / Pinterest miss | Mid-tier platforms still struggling to compete with AI-advantage of Meta/Google duopoly |\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Alphabet Q4 2025 Earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Google Search Revenue $63B - ALM Corp](https://almcorp.com/blog/google-search-63-billion-ai-mode-advertising-q4-2025/)\n- [Google posts $82.3B ad revenue - Storyboard18](https://www.storyboard18.com/advertising/google-posts-82-3-billion-of-ad-revenue-youtubes-advertising-business-hit-11-4-billion-in-q4-2025-88901.htm)\n- [Amazon Q4 ad revenue outpaces Google - eMarketer](https://www.emarketer.com/content/amazon-s-q4-ad-revenue-growth-outpaces-google--meta--spends-heavily-on-ai)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 LinkedIn - AIM Group](https://aimgroup.com/2026/02/02/microsoft-q2-fy2026-marketing-solutions-drives-linkedin-revenue-growth/)\n- [Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Apple Q4 2025 Earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/10/30/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q4-2025.html)\n- [Meta Q4 2025 Earnings - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/meta-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Meta Q4 AI-Fueled Ads Momentum - Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/meta-q4-fy-2025-results-underscore-ai-fueled-ads-momentum/)\n- [AppLovin Q4 2025 - investors.applovin.com](https://investors.applovin.com/news/news-details/2026/AppLovin-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-and-Full-Year-2025-Financial-Results/default.aspx)\n- [Trade Desk Q4 2025 - AdWeek](https://www.adweek.com/agencies/the-trade-desk-earnings-report-q4-2025/)\n- [Trade Desk stock plunges 16% - FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-2-26-growth-interrupted-the-trade-desk-shares-plummet-16-as-weak-guidance-overshadows-q4-revenue-beat)\n- [Snap Q4 2025 - Mobile Dev Memo](https://mobiledevmemo.com/snap-q4-2025-earnings-5-advertising-revenue-growth-71-subscriber-growth/)\n- [Pinterest Q4 2025 Revenue Miss - IndexBox](https://www.indexbox.io/blog/pinterest-q4-2025-results-revenue-miss-weak-2026-outlook-sparks-market-sell-off/)\n- [Ad Tech: AppLovin surge vs Trade Desk stumble - Digiday](https://digiday.com/marketing/ad-tech-briefing-applovins-ai-fueled-surge-and-the-trade-desks-stumble-show-where-investors-are-placing-their-bets/)\n- [Google AI Ads 2025 Year in Review - ALM Corp](https://almcorp.com/blog/google-ads-2025-year-in-review-updates-explained-and-2026-predictions/)\n- [IAB 2026 Outlook: 9.5% U.S. Ad Spend Growth](https://www.iab.com/news/outlook-study-forecasts-9-5-growth-in-u-s-ad-spend/)\n- [Dentsu: Global Ad Spend to surpass $1 trillion in 2026](https://www.dentsu.com/news-releases/global-ad-spend-set-to-surpass-one-trillion-for-the-first-time-in-2026-as-the-algorithmic-era-redefines-growth)\n- [Apple ATT antitrust - Gadget Hacks](https://apple.gadgethacks.com/news/apple-hit-with-986m-fine-over-privacy-policy-abuse/)\n- [Apple ATT Game-Changer Under Fire - reinouttebrake.com](https://reinouttebrake.com/2025/03/07/apples-app-tracking-transparency-a-game-changer-under-fire/)" ;
