# === memory-fd2b28dd-17f7-457d-9819-13784ad94ade ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-fd2b28dd-17f7-457d-9819-13784ad94ade> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:04:50.488885Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Microsoft Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"Search for Microsoft earnings data\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0c528c09-a4f4-4c47-b84d-8539960a4582" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:04:50.488183+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is a comprehensive summary of Microsoft's **Fiscal Q2 2026 earnings** (calendar Q4 2025, quarter ended December 31, 2025, reported January 28, 2026):\n\n---\n\n## Overall Financial Performance\n\n| Metric | Result | YoY Change |\n|--------|--------|------------|\n| Total Revenue | **$81.3 billion** | +17% (+15% CC) |\n| Operating Income | $38.3 billion | +21% |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.5 billion | +60% |\n| Net Income (non-GAAP) | $30.9 billion | +23% |\n| EPS (GAAP) | $5.16 | +60% |\n| EPS (non-GAAP) | **$4.14** | +24% |\n\n**vs. Analyst Estimates:** EPS beat ($4.14 actual vs. $3.97 expected, +4.3%); Revenue beat ($81.27B vs. $80.27B expected, +$1B beat).\n\n---\n\n## Segment Performance\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth |\n|---------|---------|------------|\n| Productivity & Business Processes | $34.1B | +16% |\n| Intelligent Cloud | **$32.9B** | +29% |\n| More Personal Computing | $14.3B | -3% |\n\n- **Azure growth: +39% YoY (+38% constant currency)** — slightly above analyst consensus of ~38.9–39.4%\n- Microsoft Cloud total crossed **$50 billion** for the first time (+26% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## AI & Copilot Metrics\n\n- **Microsoft 365 Copilot**: 15 million+ paid seats; daily active users up **10x YoY**; seat adds up **160% YoY**\n- CEO Satya Nadella: *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n- Key quote: *\"You can think of agents as the new apps\"*\n- Added nearly **1 gigawatt of total data center capacity** in the quarter alone; 50% throughput increase for OpenAI inferencing workloads\n\n---\n\n## Capital Expenditure\n\n- **CapEx: $37.5 billion** — up ~66% YoY; ~two-thirds on short-lived assets (GPUs/CPUs)\n\n---\n\n## Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n\n- Revenue guidance: **$80.65B–$81.75B** (midpoint $81.2B, in line with LSEG consensus)\n- Azure growth guidance: **37–38% constant currency** (vs. StreetAccount consensus 37.1%)\n\n---\n\n## Notable Items & Market Reaction\n\n- **Commercial bookings**: +230% YoY — heavily driven by OpenAI's **$250 billion cloud commitment** to Microsoft; ~45% of commercial RPO is from OpenAI\n- **Stock reaction**: Shares fell ~7% in after-hours trading despite the beat — investors concerned about **slowing Azure growth** (39% in Q2 vs. 40% in Q1) and heavy CapEx spending\n- Shareholder returns: $12.7 billion (dividends + buybacks, +32% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## Management Commentary Highlights\n\n- Satya Nadella framed the quarter as AI infrastructure scaling (\"AI super factory\" Fairwater data centers, AI WAN)\n- Broad demand characterized as being in \"beginning phases of AI diffusion and its broad GDP impact\"\n- TAM expected to \"grow substantially across every layer of the tech stack\"\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Press Release – Microsoft Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [Microsoft Cloud and AI strength drives second quarter results – Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Microsoft Q2 FY2026: Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC – Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [Microsoft (MSFT) Q2 Earnings Report 2026 – CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Microsoft Q2 Earnings Call Highlights – Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-call-highlights-010010532.html)\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Segment Results – Microsoft Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/segment-revenues)\n- [Microsoft's AI Growth Drives Both Revenue and Massive CapEx – PYMNTS](https://www.pymnts.com/earnings/2026/microsofts-ai-growth-drives-both-revenue-and-massive-capital-expenditure/)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "4fc1f6ae-16c9-4551-a69b-f6056adfd500" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a comprehensive summary of Microsoft's **Fiscal Q2 2026 earnings** (calendar Q4 2025, quarter ended December 31, 2025, reported January 28, 2026):\n\n---\n\n## Overall Financial Performance\n\n| Metric | Result | YoY Change |\n|--------|--------|------------|\n| Total Revenue | **$81.3 billion** | +17% (+15% CC) |\n| Operating Income | $38.3 billion | +21% |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.5 billion | +60% |\n| Net Income (non-GAAP) | $30.9 billion | +23% |\n| EPS (GAAP) | $5.16 | +60% |\n| EPS (non-GAAP) | **$4.14** | +24% |\n\n**vs. Analyst Estimates:** EPS beat ($4.14 actual vs. $3.97 expected, +4.3%); Revenue beat ($81.27B vs. $80.27B expected, +$1B beat).\n\n---\n\n## Segment Performance\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth |\n|---------|---------|------------|\n| Productivity & Business Processes | $34.1B | +16% |\n| Intelligent Cloud | **$32.9B** | +29% |\n| More Personal Computing | $14.3B | -3% |\n\n- **Azure growth: +39% YoY (+38% constant currency)** — slightly above analyst consensus of ~38.9–39.4%\n- Microsoft Cloud total crossed **$50 billion** for the first time (+26% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## AI & Copilot Metrics\n\n- **Microsoft 365 Copilot**: 15 million+ paid seats; daily active users up **10x YoY**; seat adds up **160% YoY**\n- CEO Satya Nadella: *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n- Key quote: *\"You can think of agents as the new apps\"*\n- Added nearly **1 gigawatt of total data center capacity** in the quarter alone; 50% throughput increase for OpenAI inferencing workloads\n\n---\n\n## Capital Expenditure\n\n- **CapEx: $37.5 billion** — up ~66% YoY; ~two-thirds on short-lived assets (GPUs/CPUs)\n\n---\n\n## Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n\n- Revenue guidance: **$80.65B–$81.75B** (midpoint $81.2B, in line with LSEG consensus)\n- Azure growth guidance: **37–38% constant currency** (vs. StreetAccount consensus 37.1%)\n\n---\n\n## Notable Items & Market Reaction\n\n- **Commercial bookings**: +230% YoY — heavily driven by OpenAI's **$250 billion cloud commitment** to Microsoft; ~45% of commercial RPO is from OpenAI\n- **Stock reaction**: Shares fell ~7% in after-hours trading despite the beat — investors concerned about **slowing Azure growth** (39% in Q2 vs. 40% in Q1) and heavy CapEx spending\n- Shareholder returns: $12.7 billion (dividends + buybacks, +32% YoY)\n\n---\n\n## Management Commentary Highlights\n\n- Satya Nadella framed the quarter as AI infrastructure scaling (\"AI super factory\" Fairwater data centers, AI WAN)\n- Broad demand characterized as being in \"beginning phases of AI diffusion and its broad GDP impact\"\n- TAM expected to \"grow substantially across every layer of the tech stack\"\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Press Release – Microsoft Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [Microsoft Cloud and AI strength drives second quarter results – Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Microsoft Q2 FY2026: Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC – Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [Microsoft (MSFT) Q2 Earnings Report 2026 – CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Microsoft Q2 Earnings Call Highlights – Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-call-highlights-010010532.html)\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Segment Results – Microsoft Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/segment-revenues)\n- [Microsoft's AI Growth Drives Both Revenue and Massive CapEx – PYMNTS](https://www.pymnts.com/earnings/2026/microsofts-ai-growth-drives-both-revenue-and-massive-capital-expenditure/)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] Here is a comprehensive summary of Microsoft's **Fiscal Q2 2026 earnings** (cale" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


